1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:03,400
I won't let you live.

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:05,136
I'm going to break those hands of yours.

3
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:08,840
Those hands that dared
to touch her, I'm going to shatter them!

4
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:10,320
You can't do anything.

5
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:12,560
Show me Mercan!

6
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:14,720
Don't be scared!

7
00:00:14,840 --> 00:00:15,840
Never!
I will find you.

8
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:17,680
Alright.

9
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:21,880
Look, be a man for once in your life.

10
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:23,680
Your business is with me.

11
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:29,160
Let go of
Mercan, I'll come. Let's settle our scores.

12
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:32,160
You can only talk tough
from a distance, that's all you can do.

13
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,080
Yiğit, come to the location I'll send you.

14
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,200
He recently bought a plot of land.

15
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:39,240
If he hasn't taken Mercan
and fled immediately,

16
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:40,800
he's still there.

17
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:43,160
I think he'll set a trap for Ateş.

18
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:47,960
Mercan!

19
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,280
The only
thing I'll remember is your disgustingness.

20
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:53,920
And this will be
the last thing you remember too.

21
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:56,160
Mercan!

22
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:57,680
Ah!

23
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:04,720
My brave wife.
I’ll kill him, you hear me? I’ll kill him.

24
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:06,960
He will never be able to hurt you again.

25
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:10,320
We need to catch Nezir.

26
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:14,240
Don’t worry, brother. What have we ever set
our minds to and failed?

27
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:16,080
The police are already after him too.

28
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,440
You leave Nezir aside for now.

29
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:18,920
Focus on Mercan.

30
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:22,240
She’s come back from the brink of death too
many times lately.

31
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:23,720
Where is he?

32
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:25,280
Demet, please.

33
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,360
Cemal, whatever he did,
he is still my brother.

34
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:31,600
Demet, your brother needs to surrender.

35
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:36,960
I should have killed you from the start.

36
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:42,600
If you don’t kill me here and now, I’ll be
on your neck until you die, Ateş.

37
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:43,760
Shut your mouth!

38
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:51,160
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

39
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:54,480
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

40
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:57,319
And now we reach the end.

41
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:59,239
This isn't something to watch alone.

42
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:01,559
This is something we experience together.

43
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:07,120
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

44
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:10,680
They will premiere
on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

45
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,199
One moment.

46
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:15,079
One story. One ending.

47
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,639
So grab your comfy blanket and a
huge bucket

48
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:20,640
of popcorn for one final twist.

49
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,720
Let's be there together.

50
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:15,640
Don’t do it!

51
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:24,000
Mercan, what are you doing here? I told you
to stay home.

52
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:30,040
I came because
I was afraid you might get hurt.

53
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,360
Mercan, move away from here!

54
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,720
No! I won’t let you become a killer!

55
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:46,600
I told you to step back, Mercan!

56
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,160
I said I wouldn’t step back either!

57
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:53,560
Enough! Pull the trigger! Come on, pull it!

58
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:02,640
Don’t listen to him!
He’s trying to provoke you, don’t listen!

59
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:07,880
This man deserves to die!

60
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:11,520
See, you’re right! I hate him too!

61
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:14,160
He doesn’t even deserve a single breath!

62
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,480
But if you kill him, you won’t win
this fight, Ateş!

63
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:19,200
On the contrary, you will lose!

64
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,920
You’ll go to prison!
We’ll be apart for years!

65
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:29,880
Don’t destroy everything
we dreamed of! Please, don’t do this to us!

66
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,160
Mercan, move away from here!

67
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,120
Mercan, step back!

68
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,320
Step aside, leave me alone with him!

69
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,160
Step back, I know!

70
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:50,120
I know!
From now on, we’ll have a beautiful life!

71
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,040
I know you’re afraid for me too!

72
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,240
Why would I be afraid for you?

73
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,120
You’re the real coward!

74
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,880
You’re bluffing too, I know!

75
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,400
There’s only one way to find out!

76
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,720
Mercan, move!

77
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,760
Step back, leave me alone with him!

78
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,400
Go on, shoot!

79
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,040
Shoot, go on!

80
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,600
Give him what he wants!

81
00:05:49,601 --> 00:05:52,320
What he wants is to separate us anyway!

82
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,880
Let me shoot him then!

83
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,240
Mercan, what are you doing? Drop that gun!

84
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:13,240
I’m the one who should
shoot him for kidnapping and hurting me!

85
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,840
Mercan, put down the gun!

86
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,480
You, especially!

87
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,120
You!

88
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:35,480
You can’t shoot me!

89
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,040
You won’t hurt me!

90
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,720
I’ll hit you so hard!

91
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,160
I’ll shoot you so hard!

92
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:56,456
Mercan, don’t be ridiculous, put down the
gun!

93
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,480
Step back!

94
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,520
It’s not ridiculous when you do it, so why
is it when I do?

95
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,200
Mercan, put down the gun!

96
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,240
Don’t come closer!

97
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,360
I’ll kill him!

98
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,560
Mercan!

99
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:48,960
Ateş!

100
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,280
I caught him!

101
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,000
Ateş!

102
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,640
Mercan, are you okay?

103
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,040
Are you okay?

104
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,840
Mercan, what are you doing?

105
00:07:58,560 --> 00:08:00,400
How can you put yourself in such danger?

106
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:01,880
But you are!

107
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,520
Thank God you arrived safely!

108
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:51,680
I
Was about to lose my mind waiting for you!

109
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:55,760
To the room?

110
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,040
Yes!

111
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,840
The girl won’t open her mouth!

112
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,080
Clearly, she’s very upset!

113
00:09:17,081 --> 00:09:18,601
She has gone through very hard things!

114
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,640
Your turn will come too!

115
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:29,040
Why do you act on your own, Ateş?

116
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,600
Why don’t you wait for me?

117
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:37,800
We’ve been through so much,
and you still don’t get it. Let me explain!

118
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,040
This Nezir guy is a complete psychopath!

119
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,400
What if something happened to you, Ateş?

120
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:43,760
What could I do?

121
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,320
I was going to teach him a lesson!

122
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,880
I was going to kill that bastard!

123
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,280
When Mercan arrived, I let him escape!

124
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,240
You still say you would have killed him!

125
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,960
God, give me patience!

126
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,439
Your
job is not to chase Nezir, that’s my job!

127
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,240
You’ll leave it to me, I’ll handle it!

128
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,280
You go take care of Mercan!

129
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,640
I can’t help it, Cemal, I can’t stay put!

130
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:11,600
Thinking about what Mercan did makes me go
crazy!

131
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:14,160
You have to stop,
Ateş! You must stop if necessary!

132
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,400
Stop for Mercan, stop for me!

133
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,520
You have no right to hurt that girl!

134
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,840
You have no right to leave me an orphan!

135
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,960
What if something happens to you?

136
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,800
I have to protect all of you!

137
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,560
Fine, I’m not saying anything against her,
Ateş!

138
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,960
But please don’t do this, brother!

139
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,200
Keep your mind focused… Don’t enter alone,
don’t rush anywhere!

140
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,400
We’re afraid something might happen!

141
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,760
You’re the only one left, my family, Ateş!

142
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,480
You’re right!

143
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,320
Mercan is very upset too!

144
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,280
She didn’t say a word the whole way!

145
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:03,120
What could she do?
Applaud? What were you expecting?

146
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:06,080
Ateş,
for God’s sake, listen to your sister!

147
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,680
Mercan is
very upset when you act like this!

148
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,680
The police are after Nezir, and we are too!

149
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,800
Don’t worry, we’ll find him soon!

150
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:19,440
You go
take care of Mercan, leave the rest to me!

151
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:22,680
Don’t think about this place!

152
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:29,840
Fine!

153
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,200
I still don’t understand!

154
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:52,200
How did my mother
change her attitude 180 degrees like this?

155
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,040
I don’t understand!

156
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:57,880
Why? She wouldn’t want to lose her child.

157
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,240
I don’t think that’s the case!

158
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,920
I know my mother very well!

159
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:11,960
There must
be a reason behind this change in attitude!

160
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,480
I agree with Malik!

161
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:19,520
Ayşe Hanım is not the
type to suddenly change her mind!

162
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,000
She definitely has a plan!

163
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,720
Why are you all thinking so negatively?

164
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:28,360
People can realize their mistakes and find
the right path, they can change!

165
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,680
Aren’t you the best example of that?

166
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,080
Çiçek!

167
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:39,600
Stop right there, sister!

168
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:42,360
You always twist every unpleasant event!

169
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,960
You immediately give an example, huh!

170
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:48,720
My wife is like a wingless angel, really!

171
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:56,759
Okay, like a
wingless angel, fine, I won’t say anything!

172
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,240
I didn’t say anything bad anyway!

173
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,656
I
Just said she decided to be a good person!

174
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,720
So what’s wrong with that?

175
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,520
Never mind!

176
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,120
Let’s think carefully!

177
00:13:06,121 --> 00:13:08,360
Let the ending be good, God willing!

178
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:20,320
Come on! Have your breakfast, we have work
to do!

179
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,320
Malik!

180
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,440
Malik!

181
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,280
Hey! Come on, my boy!

182
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:37,520
Alright, then I’ll make the tea!

183
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,160
Shall we talk a bit?

184
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,040
There’s nothing to talk about!

185
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:20,040
There is, for me!

186
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,560
I told you to stay in this mansion!

187
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:24,160
Why did you come?

188
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:26,080
What if something happened to you?

189
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,480
What would I do?

190
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:28,960
And what about me?

191
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,136
If something happened to you, what would I
do?

192
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,480
Have you ever thought about this?

193
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,200
I was terrified when you left like that in
a rage!

194
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,840
I was afraid Nezir would harm you!

195
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,280
I was afraid he would hurt you!

196
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:41,440
I was afraid I would never see you again!

197
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:44,840
Don’t you understand, I can’t live without
you, don’t you understand this?

198
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,640
If I hadn’t arrived, you would have become
a killer!

199
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:52,320
You would have gone to
prison as a bloody murderer!

200
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,640
Then maybe we would have
been apart for years!

201
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,336
Haven’t you ever thought about us?

202
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,840
Haven’t you thought about our future?

203
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:03,480
I did! I
did everything because I thought about it!

204
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,640
And you?

205
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,439
What went through your
mind when you pointed the gun at Nezir?

206
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:11,640
You thought about us,
and I thought about us too while doing it!

207
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,320
Did you think I would
just let you go to prison?

208
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:18,480
Mercan, you were going to become a killer!

209
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,960
Was I
supposed to go to prison so you wouldn’t?

210
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,240
Mercan, don’t! Don’t ever do this again!

211
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:30,440
If it happened again, I would do it again!

212
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,360
Hasbünallah! You won’t do it!

213
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,399
I will do it, not you!

214
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,080
Because I do everything for you!

215
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,320
I would die and I would kill too!

216
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,640
Period!

217
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:46,560
Because I don’t want
to feel the fear of losing you ever again!

218
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,480
I do everything for you too!

219
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,280
Is it really that hard to understand this?

220
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:59,520
A world without you is hell for me!

221
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,280
If you’re not there, I’m not either!

222
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,600
Period!

223
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:07,600
Give it to me!

224
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:10,600
What are you doing?

225
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,680
Am
I not even allowed to drink water anymore?

226
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,800
I won’t let you drink cold water!

227
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,080
Because I don’t want you to get sick!

228
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:35,720
Thank you.

229
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,280
Does this mean you forgive me?

230
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:53,080
Don’t count on it.

231
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:59,160
Because I don’t
think I could forgive you for a long time.

232
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:05,880
I also don’t
think I could forgive you for a long time.

233
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,400
If not forgiving is the case, what should I
do?

234
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:13,120
Alright, then we’ll stay mad at each other.
What do you say?

235
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:16,400
Fine by me. But you went first.

236
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,760
If it’s about apologizing,
you need to apologize first.

237
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:21,960
Whether I forgive or not is up to me.

238
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,440
I’m sorry.

239
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:32,760
Alright, I’m sorry too.

240
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:35,600
But I still don’t forgive you.

241
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,720
Hasbünallah, patience!

242
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,840
Don’t deprive me of yourself.

243
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,720
Did you hear me?

244
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:55,000
When I love you this much, would
I ever want to hurt you?

245
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,480
You’re right, it was a crazy thing I did.

246
00:18:58,120 --> 00:19:03,439
But the fear of losing
you ran through my bones…

247
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,680
I lost control.

248
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,920
You won’t lose control or anything, sir.

249
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,320
Look into my eyes.

250
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:18,920
I said, look into my eyes.

251
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,440
Does this mean you forgive me?

252
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:41,840
Yes, but give me a promise.

253
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:48,400
You won’t make me feel such fear again.

254
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,800
Promise, but you will
give me a promise too.

255
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,920
You will never go against my word again.

256
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:58,040
Even though I told you
to stay in the mansion, you followed me.

257
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,600
What if this was a trap?

258
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,280
You won’t take up a gun again.

259
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,160
I don’t believe you.

260
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,040
You’re still trying to make me feel guilty.

261
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,960
Your apology is bigger than your fault,
Ateş Bey.

262
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:16,920
Before you regret
forgiving me, get lost from here.

263
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:18,760
Alright, alright.

264
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,640
I was scared of you, I’m leaving.

265
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:22,640
If you miss me,

266
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:26,840
if you want to see me,

267
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:30,040
if you want to hug me,

268
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:32,920
I’ll be in the study.

269
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,920
I think Ayşe Hanım is overacting.

270
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,440
She hasn’t softened at all.

271
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,040
Çiçek is too naive.

272
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,560
Don’t fall into that woman’s trap, I think.

273
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,520
Otherwise, she’ll be the one hurt.

274
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:06,880
Oh mom.

275
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,760
You didn’t say a single word.

276
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:14,880
You’ve been strange lately.

277
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,640
You clearly have a problem.

278
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,080
Come on,
tell me so we can find a solution together.

279
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:32,520
Oh, oh.

280
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:36,560
This is such a problem that it has no cure.

281
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:39,520
It will go with me to the grave.

282
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:41,800
And it has no cure.

283
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:45,560
My
Dear mother, don’t dismiss it so quickly.

284
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,240
Remember, two minds are better than one.

285
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:50,480
And sometimes,

286
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,960
if we put our heads together, maybe we can
find a solution.

287
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,280
If only I believed there was a solution.

288
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,000
But there isn’t.

289
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:04,840
I swear I’m very sad, mother.

290
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,960
This problem
is devouring you before our eyes.

291
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,760
You acted like a mother to me.

292
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:21,680
You protected me from
Müzeyyen Hanım’s cruelty.

293
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:23,800
I can never repay your rights.

294
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,520
I
Want to be your partner in this suffering.

295
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:32,360
Even if we can’t find a solution,
at least you can tell me and feel relieved.

296
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,320
Or do you not trust me?

297
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:41,680
I swear on it, my eyes are yours, I won’t
tell anyone anything.

298
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:44,200
Fair's fair.

299
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,480
At first, I wouldn’t have trusted either.

300
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:51,240
And when you first
arrived, you gave me a lot of trouble.

301
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:55,080
Look, now you’ve softened completely.

302
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:58,200
You are also a member of the Güneş family.

303
00:22:58,680 --> 00:22:59,840
I trust you completely.

304
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:02,640
Thank you, my dear mother.

305
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,240
You made me very happy.

306
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:19,360
What’s up?

307
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,800
What are you doing?

308
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:24,760
Zehra.
Çiçek!

309
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:28,280
Look, are you trying to take my mother away
from me or what?

310
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,560
Don’t
be afraid, don’t be afraid, sister-in-law.

311
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:33,000
Binnaz mother is enough for both of us.

312
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,400
That’s enough, of course.

313
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,480
My mother is precious.

314
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,240
Oh, my little ones.

315
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,640
You’ve puffed up my chairs.

316
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:52,199
I swear, I had a nightmare last night.

317
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,400
I can’t understand what this man has done.

318
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:57,040
Once, he cornered me, strangled me, almost
killed me.

319
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:00,280
Why are you laughing, as if he didn’t hit
you too?

320
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,200
That Nezir, thank God the staff here…

321
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:08,160
Anyway, Zahide Hanım is here, I won’t talk.

322
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:11,440
Honestly, guys, he really is strange.

323
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:14,480
The man we lived under
the same roof with suddenly turned crazy.

324
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,000
Unbelievable.

325
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:19,680
I knew Nezir was sinister, but I
didn’t expect this much.

326
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:21,640
We had no safety here.

327
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:24,600
He’s really terrifying.

328
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:30,400
Oh my, open that phone already.

329
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,240
Sweetheart, are you okay?

330
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:37,320
Not at all. I can’t reach my
brother, no matter how many times I called.

331
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,800
I still don’t know what’s going on.

332
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:43,240
Should I try calling Ateş
Bey too, maybe he’s okay?

333
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:52,560
Who are you calling?

334
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:56,839
My brother. I’m trying but I can’t reach
him.

335
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:59,200
Do you know what happened?

336
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,120
Your brother escaped.

337
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:07,520
What about the Mercans? Are they okay?

338
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:09,560
They’re fine, thank God. Both are fine.

339
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,120
Oh, thank God.

340
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:14,320
Just a little shaken, naturally.

341
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:21,200
If I hadn’t heard that phone conversation,
wouldn’t you have told me?

342
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:24,920
Despite all the wrongs your brother
did, would you have hidden it from me?

343
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:29,680
There’s nothing defensible about
what he did.

344
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:31,320
I know.

345
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:35,320
But he is a piece of my life.

346
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:42,200
Not just
my brother, but also my mother and father.

347
00:25:43,320 --> 00:25:44,920
The only close one I have in life.

348
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:48,240
Is it
easy to hand over someone you love so much?

349
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,920
Deliver them with your own hands
to their executioner?

350
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:56,480
I know, it’s hard.

351
00:25:58,080 --> 00:26:00,120
Not long
ago, I went through the same paths myself.

352
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:02,879
Even if I don’t agree with you…

353
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:04,160
…I understand you very well.

354
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,840
But you also need to understand me, Demet.

355
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,120
Look, Ateş is more than a brother to me.

356
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:13,120
Mercan feels the same way.

357
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:16,400
No matter what, I won’t let them get hurt.

358
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:31,760
Take care.

359
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,200
Thank you.

360
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,520
I’m very tired.

361
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:41,200
My knees have no strength left, my head is
splitting.

362
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,800
Binnaz Hanım, bring me some water.

363
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,680
Of course, I’ll bring it right away.

364
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:09,800
I went to visit my husband and son’s grave.

365
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:13,280
I hadn’t been for a long time, it weighed
on me.

366
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:20,120
Is the late Murat’s mother really
Müzeyyen Hanım?

367
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:26,639
Every time I go to the grave…

368
00:27:26,640 --> 00:27:30,640
…my anger grows at that monster who took my
husband and son.

369
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:35,960
I endured this pain fueled
by the fire of revenge all this time.

370
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:38,720
Thanks to him, I stayed standing.

371
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:44,600
This fire won’t go out even before that man
is buried.

372
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:50,480
May God give you patience, Müzeyyen Hanım.

373
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:57,960
I wanted to get something from the kitchen
in the other mansion, with your permission.

374
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,840
Of course, of course. Go ahead.

375
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,400
Ateş!

376
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:27,880
Ateş!

377
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:37,960
Ateş!

378
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:50,960
Ateş!

379
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:56,880
Thank God you’re okay.
Thank God I found you.

380
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:04,640
I’m fine,
don’t worry. Why did you panic like that?

381
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,839
Why did I panic?

382
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:10,800
What kind of question is that? I was afraid
you’d do something crazy.

383
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:13,160
Why do you disappear without telling me?

384
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,840
I didn’t disappear.

385
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:19,520
I
Was overwhelmed at home. I went for a walk.

386
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:24,200
You’re not going anywhere without telling
me again, okay?

387
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:27,040
I can’t bear losing you.

388
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:35,280
Don’t
worry. I won’t leave you and go anywhere.

389
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:39,880
I can’t go.

390
00:29:41,800 --> 00:29:43,040
Don’t go anywhere.

391
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:23,240
Should we watch a movie
or something? It’ll help clear our minds.

392
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:29,599
I think that would
be good. A very good horror movie came out.

393
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,920
Seems
really good. If you want, let’s watch it.

394
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:35,200
Horror movie? Are you serious?

395
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:38,520
Our life is scary enough already.

396
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:41,400
I think you should choose the movie.

397
00:30:42,280 --> 00:30:43,600
Alright, let it be.

398
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:49,760
There was an actor I liked, his new
movie came out. Let’s watch it.

399
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:52,120
Again that actor?

400
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:55,600
Yes,
again him. Come on, let’s watch it in bed.

401
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:59,280
We see him more than our relatives. Aren’t
you tired of it?

402
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:04,800
Why would I be tired? He’s a very talented
actor.

403
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:09,000
Plus, he’s handsome and charismatic.

404
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:14,559
I’m tired of watching
him now. And I have a favorite actor too…

405
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:17,199
Very attractive too, actually.

406
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:20,160
You know him already, I showed him to you.

407
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,160
His new movie came out, let’s watch it.

408
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:26,960
You’ll only see that movie in your dreams,
Ateş Bey.

409
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:34,680
No, even in your dreams
you can’t see it. It’s forbidden for you.

410
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:43,080
I don’t intend to watch that actor again.
Really.

411
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:45,520
I
Don’t intend to watch that actress either.

412
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:48,720
Alright, then let’s watch the horror movie
I suggested first.

413
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:54,680
If you’re scared, of course.

414
00:31:56,960 --> 00:32:00,360
Am I supposed
to be scared of a fictional story? No way.

415
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:03,040
Alright, open it, let’s watch.

416
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:06,040
Agreed.

417
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:40,520
You’re not watching though?

418
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:42,720
I’m watching, look.

419
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,840
But if you do it
like this, you won’t understand the movie.

420
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:49,160
You need to
focus properly. You’re looking elsewhere.

421
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:50,759
I hear the sounds and understand.

422
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:53,480
But you need to watch
here. If you don’t want, we won’t watch.

423
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:56,040
Alright, fine. I’m watching.

424
00:33:23,320 --> 00:33:25,280
What’s wrong? Why did you grab my arm?

425
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:28,680
Were you scared? Come on, admit it.

426
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:32,360
Yes, I was scared.

427
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:36,200
Why are you laughing? Did it feel so good?

428
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,200
You accepted defeat for the first time.

429
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:43,720
If you allow me, I want to enjoy this.

430
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:45,720
Good.

431
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:51,000
What can I do? Paranormal
stories make me nervous.

432
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:52,320
I don’t like it.

433
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:56,440
When ghosts get involved, I get uneasy.

434
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:03,280
Mercan?

435
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:06,520
I have bad news for you.

436
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,040
What?

437
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:10,480
There’s something strange in this house.

438
00:34:11,240 --> 00:34:17,160
I don’t know whether to call
it a spirit, a demon, or just weird beings.

439
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:23,360
Nonsense. There’s no such thing.
You’re making it up to scare me.

440
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:24,960
Okay.

441
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:29,320
Then the window suddenly opening.

442
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:37,360
The door creaking for
no reason, curtains moving unexpectedly…

443
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:39,200
What do you call these?

444
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:43,800
What do you say?

445
00:34:45,680 --> 00:34:46,280
Stop joking.

446
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,320
I’ll protect you, my wife. Come here.

447
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:52,200
Come, my wife. My beautiful wife.

448
00:34:56,520 --> 00:34:57,520
Love it.

449
00:34:58,760 --> 00:34:59,760
Of course, love it.

450
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:04,120
Don’t try to run.

451
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:07,800
In a place so dark no one is here…

452
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,240
Then the spirits come.

453
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:12,800
Suddenly your face twists, you just freeze.

454
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,560
Don’t do that, Ateş.

455
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:22,600
No, I don’t want you to get hurt. Otherwise
your face could get twisted.

456
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,200
Your hands could stay bent like this.

457
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:25,840
You’re joking, okay.

458
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:53,960
What are you thinking?

459
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:57,760
About my mother.

460
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:01,960
Tomorrow I’ll go and try to understand her
intentions.

461
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:05,400
Don’t you think you’re
being a bit paranoid?

462
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,520
She came and apologized
in front of everyone.

463
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:13,400
Is being virtuous this easy? Why
are you still questioning? I don’t get it.

464
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:19,520
Because I
know my mother better than you do.

465
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:23,080
She’s not a woman who gives up so easily.

466
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:28,800
I
Don’t want the same things to happen again.

467
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,280
I don’t want anyone to be upset.

468
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:34,000
That’s why I want to be cautious.

469
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:40,280
Honestly, if I were your mother and my son
doubted me like this, I’d be really angry.

470
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:42,080
I’d probably leave.

471
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,440
Don’t overanalyze anymore.

472
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,240
Believe in your mother’s goodwill.

473
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:51,640
I don’t want anything to
go wrong just when things are finally okay.

474
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:55,400
Everything will be fine. I believe that.

475
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:00,520
I don’t know.

476
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:03,640
Maybe you’re right.

477
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:32,000
When she turned her back and almost
faced the ghost, I was so scared.

478
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:34,560
I had to hold myself back from screaming.

479
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:37,640
It was a great scene,
but I think she handled it very well.

480
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:41,040
Take this.

481
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:42,720
Thank goodness it’s over.

482
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:13,640
Don’t bother.

483
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:16,480
It won’t open; I locked it.

484
00:38:17,200 --> 00:38:18,200
You locked it?

485
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Why?

486
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:23,280
In case you do something
crazy while I’m asleep.

487
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:26,240
I’m sure you’re still thinking about Nezir.

488
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:30,320
Mercan, I promised you.

489
00:38:30,360 --> 00:38:31,360
Don’t you trust me?

490
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:33,520
Of course I trust you.

491
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,400
Even more than myself.

492
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:39,440
But I
know what you can do when anger takes over.

493
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:43,120
That’s why you’ll sleep under lock for a
while.

494
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:47,000
Do you think this can stop me?

495
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:51,640
Once I want to get out, I’ll break the door
and get out anyway.

496
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:54,560
Now stop this silly attitude of yours.

497
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:57,520
Try breaking it.

498
00:38:57,960 --> 00:38:58,960
And see what happens.

499
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:02,080
What will happen?

500
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:03,960
Tell me.

501
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:05,560
Try it and see.

502
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:09,000
That door will stay locked until morning.

503
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,200
I won’t let you leave.

504
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:12,640
That’s it.

505
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:14,240
Mercan, open this door.

506
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:22,720
I’m not opening it.

507
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:28,240
Wait, I was going to come in.

508
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:31,040
You could have
come in if you hadn’t insisted on knocking.

509
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:36,680
Hasbünallah.

510
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,040
Hasbünallah to you too.

511
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:41,800
I’ll get my revenge for this.

512
00:39:43,680 --> 00:39:44,880
See you.

513
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:48,560
We’ll see.

514
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:50,640
We’ll see, don’t worry.

515
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:06,240
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

516
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:09,560
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

517
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:12,399
And now we reach the end.

518
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:14,319
This isn't something to watch alone.

519
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:16,639
This is something we experience together.

520
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:22,200
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

521
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:25,760
They will premiere
on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

522
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:27,279
One moment.

523
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:30,159
One story. One ending.

524
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:32,719
So grab your comfy blanket and a
huge bucket

525
00:40:32,720 --> 00:40:35,720
of popcorn for one final twist.

526
00:40:35,840 --> 00:40:37,800
Let's be there together.

527
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:48,480
My wife, well done.

528
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:51,240
My wife.

529
00:40:52,720 --> 00:40:54,600
My wife, well done, breakfast looks great.

530
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:56,600
Enjoy, sweetheart.

531
00:41:01,160 --> 00:41:02,200
Come on, eat, you eat too.

532
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:09,360
My wife prepared breakfast for me.

533
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:12,400
My beautiful wife.

534
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:13,600
Come on, eat, eat.

535
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:17,120
Berat.

536
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:21,280
You need to talk to your mother.

537
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:23,680
What is it?

538
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:29,720
She’s not well; I’m worried about her.

539
00:41:30,640 --> 00:41:31,800
She has a problem.

540
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,280
I asked, but she didn’t tell me.

541
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:34,960
You should try.

542
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:36,000
She might tell you.

543
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:38,440
You’re right, my wife.

544
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:40,120
I noticed it too, you know?

545
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:44,080
Before, Mercan wasn’t here.

546
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,360
She used that as an excuse.

547
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:48,960
Now Mercan is back.

548
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,320
Still, it doesn’t feel right.

549
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:52,240
You’re right.

550
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:54,136
I’ll talk
to her at the right time, my wife.

551
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:55,160
Don’t worry.

552
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:58,600
My dear husband.

553
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:01,680
Come on, eat.

554
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,680
I swear I’m going to eat the egg.

555
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:06,240
I swear.

556
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:10,920
Come, come.

557
00:42:12,080 --> 00:42:12,760
Enjoy your meal.

558
00:42:12,761 --> 00:42:13,960
Let’s go together.

559
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:16,320
No, we already ate something.

560
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:19,320
Then…

561
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,520
Malik, my brother.

562
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:26,120
I’m saying…

563
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:29,520
Should we speed up
your wedding preparations a bit?

564
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:31,520
These things
aren’t meant to be dragged out.

565
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:37,000
I mean, maybe one day
we’ll have our own wedding too.

566
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:39,040
Who knows?

567
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:43,160
Hop hop hop.

568
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:44,680
My servant, wait there a second.

569
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:49,000
Çiçek will be a bride with a veil.

570
00:42:52,120 --> 00:42:55,320
I’ll tie that red sash around her waist as
her brother. No other way.

571
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:05,560
Come on, can you really get married like
you’re running from a fire with my brother?

572
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:08,680
Why?

573
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:12,240
You married me like that.

574
00:43:12,480 --> 00:43:13,480
What’s wrong with that?

575
00:43:21,320 --> 00:43:23,800
I said it for that reason.

576
00:43:24,280 --> 00:43:25,080
What reason?

577
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:26,280
The egg is very good.

578
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:28,440
Don’t worry about it, brother-in-law.

579
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:32,760
Wait until the Ateş wedding is over.

580
00:43:33,160 --> 00:43:36,720
Then I’ll have
a beautiful wedding for my gorgeous bride.

581
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:41,880
Their
preparations will be done next week anyway.

582
00:43:43,200 --> 00:43:46,360
Okay, enough. Stop
bickering, we have so much to do.

583
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:49,120
Let me eat this
too, then I’m going. Let me take this too.

584
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:53,840
It really turned out well.

585
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:02,520
Just like we talked about.

586
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:06,080
Okay, brother-in-law, don’t worry. Okay.

587
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:14,119
No matter what anyone says.

588
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:18,480
I’ll give my
bride the wedding she’s been dreaming of.

589
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:23,760
No one should doubt that.

590
00:44:24,160 --> 00:44:25,200
Really?

591
00:44:27,560 --> 00:44:28,560
Okay then.

592
00:44:30,600 --> 00:44:31,600
Tea?

593
00:44:32,040 --> 00:44:33,040
Tea.

594
00:44:33,640 --> 00:44:34,160
I’ll drink.

595
00:44:34,640 --> 00:44:36,240
I’ll drink tea.

596
00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:01,200
Good morning.

597
00:45:02,560 --> 00:45:03,560
Good morning.

598
00:45:05,080 --> 00:45:06,320
Looks like we stayed like this.

599
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:08,240
Yes.

600
00:45:10,960 --> 00:45:12,000
Did you sleep well?

601
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:15,280
Like a baby.

602
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:17,520
And you?

603
00:45:19,040 --> 00:45:23,200
Well, being locked in the
room, I had no better option than sleeping.

604
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:25,800
That’s good, you got some rest.

605
00:45:29,720 --> 00:45:30,720
What time is it?

606
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:38,280
Eight.

607
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:38,800
Eight?

608
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:40,320
We’ll be late for work.

609
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:45,800
Don’t even think about it. This time I’ll
be the first in the bathroom.

610
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:47,320
Why would you go first?

611
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:49,760
I haven’t forgotten last night, Mercan.

612
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,080
You deserved it though.

613
00:45:57,520 --> 00:46:00,160
Once you start getting
ready, you don’t know when you’ll come out.

614
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:01,200
That’s made up.

615
00:46:01,720 --> 00:46:02,360
I’m not making it up.

616
00:46:02,361 --> 00:46:05,960
Last time you went to
get ready, you didn’t come out for an hour.

617
00:46:47,760 --> 00:46:50,800
Don’t think I didn’t notice you were trying
to distract me.

618
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:54,040
You cheated.

619
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,200
But I got my revenge.

620
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:58,840
You can’t do this to me.

621
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:02,200
I’ll come out, but you’ll have to wait a
bit.

622
00:47:03,040 --> 00:47:04,040
Come out quickly.

623
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:05,120
I said come out.

624
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:10,040
I’ll make you regret what you did.

625
00:47:13,520 --> 00:47:14,520
I’ll accept anything.

626
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:18,560
If you want, we can go in together.

627
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:20,800
No way.

628
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:31,120
Annoying.

629
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:32,160
Still annoying.

630
00:47:35,520 --> 00:47:37,280
And now she
says, if you want, come with me.

631
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:38,920
Why would I come in with you, crazy.

632
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:05,360
Brother?

633
00:48:06,920 --> 00:48:09,360
I’ve been calling
you since yesterday, why didn’t you answer?

634
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:15,480
What would you say to a traitor?

635
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:22,160
You betrayed me, your own brother.

636
00:48:22,520 --> 00:48:23,520
Brother.

637
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:25,240
Please, just listen.

638
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:26,360
Listen to what?

639
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:31,120
Since our parents died, have I ever looked
down on you?

640
00:48:33,280 --> 00:48:35,720
Have I ever made you doubt what I said?

641
00:48:36,480 --> 00:48:38,080
Was I not always by your side?

642
00:48:39,120 --> 00:48:40,120
What did you do?

643
00:48:42,640 --> 00:48:43,880
Was this your answer, Demet?

644
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:45,880
Please…

645
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:49,560
You’re the
only one I’ve ever called family.

646
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:52,200
Okay.

647
00:48:53,480 --> 00:48:55,240
Then talk to Mercan.

648
00:48:57,640 --> 00:48:58,760
Help me win her over.

649
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:00,680
Brother, what do you say?

650
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:02,640
I can’t.

651
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:05,800
Mercan doesn’t love you.

652
00:49:06,080 --> 00:49:07,160
She loves Ateş.

653
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:10,640
You can’t force this on anyone.

654
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:12,360
Whether forced or not.

655
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:15,680
I’m in love with her.

656
00:49:16,560 --> 00:49:17,560
Don’t you understand?

657
00:49:18,040 --> 00:49:21,400
Brother, I beg you, get your head straight.

658
00:49:24,360 --> 00:49:25,480
Is that your final word?

659
00:49:26,280 --> 00:49:27,560
Please, don’t dismiss me.

660
00:49:28,360 --> 00:49:30,160
Look, you’re making a huge mistake.

661
00:49:30,880 --> 00:49:33,040
You can’t run forever.

662
00:49:33,360 --> 00:49:35,016
You need to turn yourself in to the police.

663
00:49:35,040 --> 00:49:36,680
Shut your mouth, shut it.

664
00:49:41,560 --> 00:49:43,400
You’ve said what you wanted to say.

665
00:49:45,240 --> 00:49:46,680
Brother, please.

666
00:49:47,640 --> 00:49:49,000
I’m saying this for your own good.

667
00:49:50,280 --> 00:49:52,440
I want you to do what’s right for you.

668
00:49:53,880 --> 00:49:56,360
Don’t pretend to care about me.

669
00:49:58,120 --> 00:49:59,120
You…

670
00:49:59,840 --> 00:50:00,320
You…

671
00:50:00,321 --> 00:50:01,800
You betrayed your own brother.

672
00:50:04,040 --> 00:50:05,240
You went and chose your enemy.

673
00:50:07,080 --> 00:50:08,120
You died for me, girl.

674
00:50:09,200 --> 00:50:10,200
You’re gone now.

675
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:17,640
Brother.

676
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:19,800
Brother.

677
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:23,920
Brother, please don’t go.

678
00:50:37,760 --> 00:50:39,520
I got news about Mercan.

679
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:41,920
How is she now? Is she okay?

680
00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:44,400
She’s okay, thank God.

681
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:46,920
But I was so scared, Haydar.

682
00:50:51,280 --> 00:50:53,079
After we buried Murat…

683
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:55,440
…I was terrified something would happen to
Mercan too.

684
00:50:57,240 --> 00:51:00,920
Lately, I keep seeing Murat in my dreaMrs.

685
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:04,360
It seems
like he has no peace where he lies.

686
00:51:05,720 --> 00:51:09,120
It’s like he wants to tell me something.

687
00:51:09,760 --> 00:51:11,800
His dead
body tormented us, and the living one too.

688
00:51:12,920 --> 00:51:15,560
Whatever came upon us,
it was because of that boy.

689
00:51:17,280 --> 00:51:19,320
I can’t
believe you’re saying these things, Haydar.

690
00:51:20,240 --> 00:51:23,200
How can a father speak like this about his
dead child?

691
00:51:23,920 --> 00:51:25,200
Am I lying, Nermin?

692
00:51:26,240 --> 00:51:28,040
Don’t ever speak a word about Murat again.

693
00:51:29,440 --> 00:51:30,520
If you’re in this hole…

694
00:51:31,320 --> 00:51:34,320
…because of your other son who betrayed
us by teaming up with Ateş.

695
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:37,640
Enough already.

696
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:39,880
Know the
truth and stop being so close to the fire.

697
00:51:44,080 --> 00:51:46,360
Murat isn’t our son.

698
00:51:50,800 --> 00:51:52,800
You’ve mourned that child more than needed.

699
00:51:55,240 --> 00:51:57,240
What are you saying, Haydar?

700
00:51:57,400 --> 00:51:58,600
What nonsense are you talking?

701
00:52:02,200 --> 00:52:04,320
Murat isn’t our son, Nermin.

702
00:52:05,400 --> 00:52:06,440
He’s someone else’s child.

703
00:52:09,280 --> 00:52:11,880
No, this can’t be true!

704
00:52:12,920 --> 00:52:13,920
You’re lying.

705
00:52:16,400 --> 00:52:18,360
You’re making this up so I forget my son.

706
00:52:18,920 --> 00:52:21,040
Nermin, I’m telling you for the last time.

707
00:52:21,680 --> 00:52:23,160
Murat isn’t our son.

708
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:25,160
If you don’t believe me, go ask Binnaz.

709
00:52:25,960 --> 00:52:27,000
He’s someone else’s child.

710
00:52:28,920 --> 00:52:29,960
She’ll tell you the truth.

711
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:33,960
Where are you going, Haydar?

712
00:52:34,760 --> 00:52:36,640
Haydar, you’re lying.

713
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:39,280
Haydar, come here, you’re lying.

714
00:52:48,080 --> 00:52:49,640
This can’t be true.

715
00:52:50,720 --> 00:52:51,720
Impossible.

716
00:52:53,520 --> 00:52:54,600
Murat is my son.

717
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:00,200
He’s lying.

718
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:02,640
Murat is my son.

719
00:53:09,960 --> 00:53:13,080
It took a while, but it’ll be costly.

720
00:53:13,560 --> 00:53:14,560
I mean…

721
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:16,400
We’ll figure it out.

722
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:21,720
Welcome, Mr. Ateş.

723
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:23,200
Welcome, I hope you’re okay.

724
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:24,440
Thank you.

725
00:53:24,920 --> 00:53:25,920
Thanks.

726
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:48,280
I can’t even look at you, Mercan.

727
00:53:50,520 --> 00:53:51,760
On one side, my brother.

728
00:53:52,240 --> 00:53:54,080
On the other side, you.

729
00:53:55,800 --> 00:53:57,040
It was really hard, believe me.

730
00:53:58,320 --> 00:54:00,120
Being caught
in the middle was a heavy price.

731
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:02,640
Please, forgive me.

732
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:06,200
Yes, it was heavy.

733
00:54:08,160 --> 00:54:09,640
It could’ve been even heavier.

734
00:54:12,760 --> 00:54:14,800
Something could have happened
to Ateş, for example.

735
00:54:17,360 --> 00:54:20,840
The information you kept hidden for your
brother’s sake could have been our end, Demet.

736
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:26,320
You know me.

737
00:54:27,360 --> 00:54:29,320
You know how much I love you.

738
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:31,480
I really didn’t want it to be like this.

739
00:54:31,720 --> 00:54:33,280
I’m very sorry, Mercan.

740
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:39,400
I can’t deny it.

741
00:54:40,120 --> 00:54:41,160
I’m very angry with you.

742
00:54:45,600 --> 00:54:47,520
But at the same time, I understand you.

743
00:54:50,800 --> 00:54:55,960
A person can’t easily remove their brother,
their own flesh and blood.

744
00:54:58,360 --> 00:55:00,520
I was in the same dilemma in the past.

745
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:08,520
I understand if you don’t want to talk to
me.

746
00:55:10,680 --> 00:55:13,360
It would be good if I left the company too.

747
00:55:15,800 --> 00:55:17,360
Seeing you, I wanted to apologize.

748
00:55:20,760 --> 00:55:21,760
You can’t go anywhere.

749
00:55:25,240 --> 00:55:27,240
Will you leave me alone before the wedding?

750
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:20,920
Nobody saw you, right?

751
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:23,000
No.

752
00:56:24,920 --> 00:56:26,160
Thanks for coming.

753
00:56:27,600 --> 00:56:28,600
Why did you call me?

754
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:30,800
I need your help.

755
00:56:32,440 --> 00:56:36,280
With so many people at
your command, why me?

756
00:56:37,560 --> 00:56:39,680
Honestly, only you can help me.

757
00:56:43,560 --> 00:56:46,840
Only you can keep me informed
about what Ateş is doing.

758
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:49,840
You gave me a promise.

759
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:53,680
There shouldn't be any harm to Ateş.

760
00:56:56,080 --> 00:56:58,000
But you didn’t keep the agreement.

761
00:57:00,640 --> 00:57:03,640
Okay, you’re right. I made a mistake.

762
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:12,400
But please, let’s leave
everything behind. Let’s start a new page.

763
00:57:14,080 --> 00:57:15,400
I really need your support, Aslı.

764
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:20,600
Instead of taking Mercan and leaving,
you chose to set a trap for Ateş.

765
00:57:24,280 --> 00:57:25,640
You weren’t supposed to touch him.

766
00:57:26,040 --> 00:57:27,600
Ateş was my red line.

767
00:57:28,520 --> 00:57:31,280
You crossed that line.

768
00:57:31,920 --> 00:57:32,920
It’s too late now.

769
00:57:34,280 --> 00:57:35,360
Everything is already over.

770
00:57:36,640 --> 00:57:37,640
What do you mean?

771
00:57:39,040 --> 00:57:40,040
Won’t you fight?

772
00:57:42,640 --> 00:57:43,840
I accepted defeat.

773
00:57:45,240 --> 00:57:46,240
It’s over.

774
00:58:26,680 --> 00:58:27,680
What’s going on?

775
00:58:28,360 --> 00:58:29,360
What are you doing here?

776
00:58:30,560 --> 00:58:32,640
Are you doing renovations
in your room or something?

777
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:35,040
Oh come on,
a room between us is nothing, dear.

778
00:58:35,880 --> 00:58:39,360
I wanted to work here
today. Is there a problem?

779
00:58:40,680 --> 00:58:43,240
No problem, but don’t bother for nothing.

780
00:58:44,360 --> 00:58:45,360
I understand.

781
00:58:47,760 --> 00:58:49,280
Then tell me so I can understand too.

782
00:58:51,640 --> 00:58:55,000
You wanted to
keep me under watch. That’s why you came.

783
00:58:59,040 --> 00:59:00,120
Is that what you’re saying?

784
00:59:00,880 --> 00:59:02,200
That works for me.

785
00:59:04,440 --> 00:59:07,800
While you’re here,
you can also look at these files.

786
00:59:09,560 --> 00:59:10,920
That won’t happen, Mr. Ateş.

787
00:59:11,520 --> 00:59:13,240
Please handle your own work.

788
00:59:13,920 --> 00:59:15,440
I have a lot of work to finish.

789
00:59:15,560 --> 00:59:19,240
You can add these too. Don’t forget them.

790
00:59:21,040 --> 00:59:23,440
The files are too thick to squeeze in.

791
00:59:27,400 --> 00:59:28,400
Come.

792
00:59:33,640 --> 00:59:36,879
Sorry to bother you like this, but…

793
00:59:36,880 --> 00:59:39,320
Unfortunately, we have
an important problem.

794
00:59:40,200 --> 00:59:41,200
What is it?

795
00:59:42,200 --> 00:59:45,160
A bureaucratic obstacle
has come up with the Italy project…

796
00:59:45,200 --> 00:59:48,520
…and unfortunately, we can’t intervene from
here.

797
00:59:48,600 --> 00:59:51,360
It
Needs to be handled on-site, and urgently.

798
00:59:55,600 --> 00:59:56,960
No problem, we’ll handle it.

799
00:59:58,200 --> 01:00:00,240
How are
we going to handle it? We have to go there.

800
01:00:01,280 --> 01:00:02,920
If we need to go, we’ll go.

801
01:00:06,160 --> 01:00:07,560
Actually, not a bad idea.

802
01:00:10,720 --> 01:00:12,960
We’ll get a
short getaway before the wedding.

803
01:00:18,040 --> 01:00:21,680
Yaşar, get us two
plane tickets for the nearest date, please.

804
01:00:22,360 --> 01:00:23,440
I’ll handle it immediately.

805
01:00:29,720 --> 01:00:30,720
Then let’s go.

806
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:33,880
Let’s go.

807
01:00:34,800 --> 01:00:35,800
Let’s go, let’s go.

808
01:00:36,160 --> 01:00:38,080
Let’s go home and pack our bags.

809
01:00:40,280 --> 01:00:41,280
I’m so excited.

810
01:00:42,840 --> 01:00:44,360
We’re going to Italy together.

811
01:01:12,640 --> 01:01:14,120
Welcome.

812
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:17,999
I’ll let Malik know you arrived.

813
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:19,840
No need.

814
01:01:21,640 --> 01:01:24,200
I came to talk to you.

815
01:01:25,800 --> 01:01:27,040
Of course, please.

816
01:01:28,200 --> 01:01:32,919
I know you’re an opportunistic girl,

817
01:01:32,920 --> 01:01:37,320
that you want to marry Malik for his money.

818
01:01:39,040 --> 01:01:41,360
If you came to insult
me, you came for nothing.

819
01:01:43,920 --> 01:01:46,240
You talk a good game.

820
01:01:49,680 --> 01:01:51,960
You’re smart.

821
01:01:53,840 --> 01:01:57,120
But remember this.

822
01:01:58,320 --> 01:02:06,320
As long as I live, I’ll do everything to make
sure you don’t get a single penny from my family.

823
01:02:33,920 --> 01:02:41,920
I’ll give you a chance to prove me wrong.
If you’re sincere…

824
01:02:45,320 --> 01:02:53,320
If you really have no claims from
Malik, you’ll sign this marriage contract.

825
01:02:54,680 --> 01:03:02,680
Even after marrying, your
rights will be limited.

826
01:03:04,560 --> 01:03:09,960
If
You divorce, you won’t get a single penny.

827
01:03:12,680 --> 01:03:20,360
If
You truly love Malik, this is your chance.

828
01:03:22,680 --> 01:03:26,560
But there’s a condition.

829
01:03:30,200 --> 01:03:35,240
Never tell my son anything.

830
01:03:36,240 --> 01:03:44,240
If you
tell Malik, I’ll never let you be my bride.

831
01:03:49,440 --> 01:03:50,720
Never.

832
01:04:40,360 --> 01:04:41,680
Are you alright, Mrs. Nermin?

833
01:04:46,080 --> 01:04:47,120
Murat.

834
01:04:49,080 --> 01:04:51,200
He’s my son.

835
01:05:05,760 --> 01:05:06,760
Haydar…

836
01:05:06,800 --> 01:05:09,360
Haydar said Murat isn’t my son.

837
01:05:14,520 --> 01:05:15,520
Is this true?

838
01:05:20,880 --> 01:05:22,720
Tell me, is it true? Why are you silent?

839
01:05:35,880 --> 01:05:40,960
I’ve been living with the guilt
of this secret for years, Mrs. Nermin.

840
01:05:45,880 --> 01:05:47,440
I was afraid of Mr. Haydar.

841
01:05:48,320 --> 01:05:50,680
I couldn’t say it, I couldn’t tell you.

842
01:05:52,120 --> 01:05:53,760
Please forgive me.

843
01:05:55,040 --> 01:05:56,240
Is that true, then?

844
01:05:57,680 --> 01:05:59,560
Murat isn’t my son?

845
01:06:04,560 --> 01:06:06,039
My son…

846
01:06:06,040 --> 01:06:09,000
Then did my son die?

847
01:06:13,520 --> 01:06:15,560
He died at birth, Mrs. Nermin.

848
01:06:17,560 --> 01:06:19,400
The cord was wrapped around his neck.

849
01:06:20,680 --> 01:06:23,520
When he had to be born at home…

850
01:06:28,120 --> 01:06:30,600
Why were
you silent all these years, Binnaz?

851
01:06:31,880 --> 01:06:34,080
How did you make me believe such a lie?

852
01:06:38,360 --> 01:06:40,120
Forgive me, Mrs. Nermin.

853
01:06:41,560 --> 01:06:47,800
I swear, I honestly didn’t know Murat was
Mrs. Müzeyyen’s son.

854
01:06:49,840 --> 01:06:50,840
What?

855
01:07:06,040 --> 01:07:07,320
What are you saying, Binnaz?

856
01:07:09,560 --> 01:07:11,520
No, no, I didn’t say anything.

857
01:07:11,760 --> 01:07:12,760
I didn’t say anything.

858
01:07:14,480 --> 01:07:18,280
My Murat is Müzeyyen’s son?

859
01:07:23,320 --> 01:07:25,000
My son…

860
01:07:26,840 --> 01:07:27,680
Murat…

861
01:07:27,681 --> 01:07:28,880
Müzeyyen’s son?

862
01:07:33,080 --> 01:07:34,760
My son…

863
01:07:36,200 --> 01:07:37,040
Murat…

864
01:07:37,041 --> 01:07:38,360
Müzeyyen’s son?

865
01:07:39,160 --> 01:07:41,200
Why are you silent, answer me.

866
01:07:42,760 --> 01:07:44,640
My son is Müzeyyen’s son?

867
01:08:26,160 --> 01:08:29,519
Don’t be mad, but I’m so happy about this
Italy trip.

868
01:08:29,520 --> 01:08:33,520
I was about
to say, almost two problems in the project.

869
01:08:37,280 --> 01:08:39,680
Looks like you needed such a break.

870
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:41,160
Not just me.

871
01:08:42,200 --> 01:08:44,240
We both need a breath of fresh air.

872
01:08:46,680 --> 01:08:48,960
A
Little pre-wedding getaway for both of us.

873
01:08:49,480 --> 01:08:50,480
Yes.

874
01:08:53,480 --> 01:08:54,480
Wait a minute.

875
01:08:55,360 --> 01:08:56,360
What happened?

876
01:08:59,160 --> 01:09:00,880
I understand your worry, Mercan.

877
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:06,440
I know you
wanted to distance yourself to protect me.

878
01:09:08,480 --> 01:09:10,920
Yes, because I’m very scared for you.

879
01:09:11,680 --> 01:09:14,200
Don’t worry, I won’t
fall into Nezir’s trap.

880
01:09:15,760 --> 01:09:17,480
I won’t make the mistake of killing him.

881
01:09:18,680 --> 01:09:20,720
I’ll catch
him and turn him over to justice.

882
01:09:21,240 --> 01:09:22,240
I promise.

883
01:09:23,560 --> 01:09:25,440
But you’ll make me a promise too.

884
01:09:27,640 --> 01:09:29,560
Please, don’t be afraid anymore.

885
01:09:30,200 --> 01:09:32,080
Don’t let this emotion take control of you.

886
01:09:33,120 --> 01:09:34,640
We are stronger together.

887
01:09:36,320 --> 01:09:39,640
If you give a promise, I will too.

888
01:09:41,160 --> 01:09:43,920
I won’t let my fears control me anymore.

889
01:09:47,280 --> 01:09:49,720
After returning
from Italy, we’ll have a beautiful wedding.

890
01:09:52,080 --> 01:09:54,959
We won’t let fears ruin our best day.

891
01:09:54,960 --> 01:09:57,360
We won’t give Nezir what he wants.

892
01:09:57,880 --> 01:10:00,080
There, that’s my wife.

893
01:10:05,240 --> 01:10:06,240
My lion.

894
01:10:07,440 --> 01:10:08,440
My lion?

895
01:10:09,080 --> 01:10:10,840
Yes, you’re my lion.

896
01:10:28,000 --> 01:10:29,600
Why are you looking at me so strangely?

897
01:10:30,560 --> 01:10:31,560
You’re a killer!

898
01:10:32,120 --> 01:10:33,120
You’re a killer!

899
01:10:33,121 --> 01:10:34,560
Killer!

900
01:10:34,960 --> 01:10:35,960
You’re a killer!

901
01:10:36,280 --> 01:10:37,480
What nonsense are you talking?

902
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:39,000
Killer!

903
01:10:39,280 --> 01:10:40,280
You are the killer!

904
01:10:40,400 --> 01:10:41,400
Mom, what happened?

905
01:10:44,120 --> 01:10:46,120
Are you still there, woman?

906
01:10:48,920 --> 01:10:51,000
I didn’t kill your son or anything.

907
01:10:51,240 --> 01:10:52,440
What do I care about your son?

908
01:10:54,920 --> 01:10:55,920
True.

909
01:10:57,280 --> 01:10:59,600
You didn’t kill my son.

910
01:11:02,240 --> 01:11:04,360
Because you killed your own son.

911
01:11:05,720 --> 01:11:07,320
You are a child killer.

912
01:11:22,680 --> 01:11:24,600
Murat was your son.

913
01:11:44,640 --> 01:11:46,640
What nonsense are you
talking, this is a lie.

914
01:11:49,760 --> 01:11:51,360
But this is the truth.

915
01:11:53,160 --> 01:11:55,160
Murat was the son you thought was dead.

916
01:12:05,640 --> 01:12:08,920
Haydar took him and put him in place of my
dead son.

917
01:12:10,560 --> 01:12:11,600
You’re lying.

918
01:12:15,640 --> 01:12:16,640
No.

919
01:12:17,000 --> 01:12:18,000
Not a lie.

920
01:12:21,680 --> 01:12:23,480
Haydar fooled both of us.

921
01:12:29,040 --> 01:12:30,280
Murat was your son.

922
01:12:30,680 --> 01:12:31,680
But I was his mother.

923
01:12:34,360 --> 01:12:37,040
You killed my Murat.

924
01:12:39,000 --> 01:12:41,640
You are the real killer of your own child.

925
01:12:46,360 --> 01:12:48,280
You buried your son twice.

926
01:13:39,760 --> 01:13:40,520
Mom…

927
01:13:40,521 --> 01:13:42,400
Mom, do you realize what you’re saying?

928
01:13:43,280 --> 01:13:44,920
This can’t be real, look.

929
01:13:51,600 --> 01:13:53,120
This… What? How? How?

930
01:13:54,240 --> 01:13:55,840
What are you saying, Mrs. Nermin?

931
01:13:56,680 --> 01:13:57,680
Speak up!

932
01:14:04,920 --> 01:14:06,680
What kind of thing is this?

933
01:14:07,880 --> 01:14:09,160
It’s a very painful thing.

934
01:14:10,480 --> 01:14:12,600
Liar! You’re lying!

935
01:14:12,840 --> 01:14:14,800
What a despicable woman you are!

936
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:16,720
You found this lie, huh!

937
01:14:17,240 --> 01:14:19,280
Thinking you’ll hurt me!

938
01:14:19,640 --> 01:14:20,640
Mom Müzeyyen, stop!

939
01:14:20,680 --> 01:14:21,680
Liar!

940
01:14:21,840 --> 01:14:24,159
Look, Mrs. Nermin, if this is a lie…

941
01:14:24,160 --> 01:14:25,160
Enough!

942
01:14:26,240 --> 01:14:27,680
Enough already, leave me alone!

943
01:14:29,280 --> 01:14:31,080
I have enough troubles of my own.

944
01:14:34,120 --> 01:14:36,200
You killed my Murat.

945
01:14:38,680 --> 01:14:40,280
Murat, my son.

946
01:14:41,040 --> 01:14:42,880
You gave birth to him, but I’m the mother!

947
01:14:46,000 --> 01:14:47,880
You only gave birth to him.

948
01:14:58,280 --> 01:15:00,680
Go ask that Haydar scoundrel and
have him explain it to you!

949
01:15:01,520 --> 01:15:05,200
You even
hope for help from my dead son to harm me!

950
01:15:06,040 --> 01:15:07,479
You’re lying!

951
01:15:07,480 --> 01:15:09,040
Enough, Mom Müzeyyen!

952
01:15:09,520 --> 01:15:11,280
You’re lying! Let me go!

953
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:12,480
Mom Müzeyyen, stop!

954
01:15:13,280 --> 01:15:14,880
Stop, let’s find out what happened.

955
01:15:15,280 --> 01:15:15,720
Liar!

956
01:15:16,240 --> 01:15:18,320
Let anyone believe what they want.

957
01:15:18,840 --> 01:15:20,560
But this won’t change the truth.

958
01:15:22,480 --> 01:15:25,360
You killed my Murat, the
child you gave birth to.

959
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:34,480
You did it with your own hands.

960
01:15:36,160 --> 01:15:38,000
You saw with your own eyes that he died!

961
01:15:43,960 --> 01:15:48,080
Mom, such a thing can’t be a lie!

962
01:15:49,200 --> 01:15:54,240
Anyone who doesn’t believe
it, or wants to question it, go to Haydar!

963
01:15:59,560 --> 01:16:01,200
Cemal, don’t leave her alone!

964
01:16:07,880 --> 01:16:08,880
Mercan!

965
01:16:26,800 --> 01:16:27,880
Are you okay, beautiful?

966
01:16:28,600 --> 01:16:29,600
I’m not.

967
01:16:30,520 --> 01:16:32,760
How can anyone be okay in a situation like
this?

968
01:16:39,000 --> 01:16:40,760
There’s a huge emptiness here.

969
01:16:43,280 --> 01:16:44,280
Ice cold.

970
01:16:48,960 --> 01:16:50,400
Do you want to step away a little?

971
01:16:52,280 --> 01:16:55,040
Even if we wanted to, we
can’t step away while our minds are here.

972
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:06,600
Is there anything I can do for you?

973
01:17:09,960 --> 01:17:13,160
I want a family
that doesn’t lie to each other.

974
01:17:14,800 --> 01:17:17,159
A family without secrets, where no one

975
01:17:17,160 --> 01:17:19,760
harms anyone.

976
01:17:20,040 --> 01:17:21,040
Am I asking for too much?

977
01:17:24,880 --> 01:17:26,120
You’re not asking for too much.

978
01:18:05,480 --> 01:18:08,320
Haven’t you understood anything?

979
01:18:09,200 --> 01:18:10,440
Daughter, are you crazy?

980
01:18:11,040 --> 01:18:13,360
If I had understood until now, would I have
stayed silent?

981
01:18:16,200 --> 01:18:18,840
I have a tight mouth, but not this tight.

982
01:18:20,240 --> 01:18:22,560
Then how
did my mom keep this secret all this time?

983
01:18:23,160 --> 01:18:24,160
Honestly, I don’t know.

984
01:18:26,600 --> 01:18:27,600
All this time.

985
01:18:33,000 --> 01:18:36,120
Mom, I really want to ask you something.

986
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:38,680
How could you stay silent all this time?

987
01:18:42,840 --> 01:18:44,280
Honestly, I give up.

988
01:18:44,880 --> 01:18:46,680
Even stone would crack after all this time.

989
01:18:53,280 --> 01:18:55,080
So what are we going to do now?

990
01:18:56,400 --> 01:19:00,399
If these people
put us at the door, it wouldn’t be enough…

991
01:19:00,400 --> 01:19:03,040
The man switched the children.

992
01:19:03,640 --> 01:19:06,040
You didn’t open your mouth, didn’t utter
a word.

993
01:19:06,480 --> 01:19:08,000
Honestly, I’d be scared of you, mom.

994
01:19:08,080 --> 01:19:09,160
This can’t go on like this.

995
01:19:09,360 --> 01:19:10,360
What is this?

996
01:19:11,920 --> 01:19:12,920
Enough!

997
01:19:14,880 --> 01:19:17,040
Do any of you know what I’ve suffered all
these years?

998
01:19:21,240 --> 01:19:23,920
Do you think
it’s easy to stay silent knowing this sin?

999
01:19:25,600 --> 01:19:26,800
My troubles are enough for me.

1000
01:19:35,200 --> 01:19:36,200
What’s happening?

1001
01:19:36,800 --> 01:19:38,280
What’s going to happen?

1002
01:19:39,240 --> 01:19:40,800
The incident at the mansion isn’t over.

1003
01:19:41,080 --> 01:19:42,120
My work isn’t over either.

1004
01:19:42,960 --> 01:19:43,960
I’m leaving.

1005
01:19:45,640 --> 01:19:46,640
Unbelievable.

1006
01:19:52,160 --> 01:19:53,680
How are you?

1007
01:19:55,680 --> 01:19:56,680
We couldn’t talk at all.

1008
01:19:58,360 --> 01:20:00,240
I was going to wash the
laundry at the mansion.

1009
01:20:00,400 --> 01:20:01,400
I forgot them.

1010
01:20:01,600 --> 01:20:02,560
I’ll wash them.

1011
01:20:02,561 --> 01:20:04,040
Then we’ll talk, okay?

1012
01:20:49,960 --> 01:20:56,360
Mrs. Müzeyyen? What wind blew you here like
this?

1013
01:20:57,760 --> 01:21:00,240
Did you want
to bring your greeting yourself this time?

1014
01:21:02,520 --> 01:21:04,879
Since you called me so suddenly…

1015
01:21:04,880 --> 01:21:06,800
…the matter must be quite important.

1016
01:21:10,400 --> 01:21:11,400
Murat…
…is he my son?

1017
01:21:17,360 --> 01:21:18,720
Murat, is he my son?

1018
01:21:20,280 --> 01:21:21,440
How did you find out?

1019
01:21:23,040 --> 01:21:24,040
How?

1020
01:21:25,320 --> 01:21:26,320
Who told you?

1021
01:21:27,240 --> 01:21:28,640
Where did they know from, nonsense.

1022
01:21:29,160 --> 01:21:30,160
How?

1023
01:21:31,000 --> 01:21:32,120
Tell me!

1024
01:21:38,640 --> 01:21:40,400
I’ll tell, but on one condition.

1025
01:21:43,720 --> 01:21:45,120
I want a guarantee for my life.

1026
01:21:46,120 --> 01:21:48,120
How do I
know you won’t kill me when you find out?

1027
01:21:49,280 --> 01:21:50,280
You can’t know.

1028
01:21:51,040 --> 01:21:52,480
Then I won’t say a word.

1029
01:21:54,000 --> 01:21:55,000
Okay.

1030
01:21:56,360 --> 01:21:57,360
Okay.

1031
01:22:01,880 --> 01:22:03,880
Tell me!

1032
01:22:04,520 --> 01:22:06,680
My hair won’t be harmed.

1033
01:22:07,640 --> 01:22:09,320
Don’t drag it out, Haydar, tell me!

1034
01:22:12,920 --> 01:22:14,800
You gave birth on the same day as Nermin.

1035
01:22:16,000 --> 01:22:17,080
Our boy didn’t survive.

1036
01:22:18,400 --> 01:22:21,040
I was with
Ahmet that day, we were settling a matter.

1037
01:22:21,760 --> 01:22:23,080
You know the topic, after all.

1038
01:22:23,960 --> 01:22:25,560
He made a mistake, he paid the price.

1039
01:22:25,880 --> 01:22:26,880
Keep it short!

1040
01:22:30,120 --> 01:22:31,120
My men called.

1041
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:35,120
They said the boy had died.

1042
01:22:35,720 --> 01:22:37,440
At first, I didn’t have such an idea.

1043
01:22:37,920 --> 01:22:40,456
But when I saw your baby,
I took him and brought him to the mansion.

1044
01:22:40,480 --> 01:22:41,480
That’s it.

1045
01:22:41,520 --> 01:22:42,520
Haydar!

1046
01:22:43,360 --> 01:22:44,360
Haydar!

1047
01:22:44,840 --> 01:22:46,920
You took my son from me, Haydar!

1048
01:22:47,840 --> 01:22:49,680
Don’t you have a conscience?

1049
01:22:49,960 --> 01:22:51,200
How can you do this?

1050
01:22:51,800 --> 01:22:52,800
How?

1051
01:22:54,640 --> 01:22:56,840
Ah! If I had known my son was alive.

1052
01:22:57,880 --> 01:23:00,840
If I had
known, I would have held him once, Haydar!

1053
01:23:04,240 --> 01:23:07,120
I grieved his grave for years.

1054
01:23:07,640 --> 01:23:09,360
How did you steal my baby from me?

1055
01:23:11,320 --> 01:23:13,320
Don’t you have any conscience?

1056
01:23:13,520 --> 01:23:14,640
Don’t you have a heart?

1057
01:23:15,080 --> 01:23:16,280
I will kill you!

1058
01:23:16,840 --> 01:23:18,600
How did you take my baby from me?

1059
01:23:19,080 --> 01:23:20,720
I will kill you, Haydar!

1060
01:23:21,240 --> 01:23:24,640
May every
breath I take before burying you be cursed!

1061
01:23:25,160 --> 01:23:25,600
Let go!

1062
01:23:26,080 --> 01:23:27,840
Haydar, I will kill you!

1063
01:23:29,800 --> 01:23:30,839
I will kill you!

1064
01:23:30,840 --> 01:23:32,280
Let me go!

1065
01:23:49,400 --> 01:23:50,440
I can’t believe it.

1066
01:23:51,520 --> 01:23:53,240
My mind can’t grasp it.

1067
01:23:56,200 --> 01:23:57,200
Me neither.

1068
01:23:57,720 --> 01:23:59,680
There’s a secret hidden all this time.

1069
01:24:00,440 --> 01:24:02,680
This much is too much now.

1070
01:24:05,640 --> 01:24:08,879
Oh, my brother…

1071
01:24:08,880 --> 01:24:11,120
My brother was Mrs. Müzeyyen’s son.

1072
01:24:13,320 --> 01:24:16,480
What
kind of evil is this? What kind of cruelty?

1073
01:24:19,920 --> 01:24:23,280
Poor brother,
he died without learning his real parents.

1074
01:24:26,720 --> 01:24:27,520
Moreover…

1075
01:24:27,521 --> 01:24:29,439
Maybe it’s a lie.

1076
01:24:29,440 --> 01:24:31,040
Not something they wouldn’t do.

1077
01:24:33,600 --> 01:24:35,200
My mother wouldn’t lie about this.

1078
01:24:38,400 --> 01:24:41,880
And sadly, I
can’t say my father wouldn’t do this much.

1079
01:24:42,960 --> 01:24:44,920
Honestly, I didn’t expect this either.

1080
01:24:48,200 --> 01:24:49,719
If it’s true…

1081
01:24:49,720 --> 01:24:51,200
Mom Müzeyyen will be very upset.

1082
01:24:53,000 --> 01:24:54,800
This truth will hurt everyone.

1083
01:24:56,400 --> 01:24:58,719
Actually, the son she thought was dead…

1084
01:24:58,720 --> 01:25:00,560
…was right in front of her eyes.

1085
01:25:01,400 --> 01:25:05,000
Moreover, for revenge,
she sacrificed her own son.

1086
01:25:06,520 --> 01:25:08,320
I’m very scared of what’s to come.

1087
01:25:09,880 --> 01:25:13,039
I think this time it can’t get worse, but…

1088
01:25:13,040 --> 01:25:15,360
…every time, something worse appears.

1089
01:25:16,120 --> 01:25:18,000
What
does it mean to take someone else’s child?

1090
01:25:18,720 --> 01:25:19,720
How can this happen?

1091
01:25:25,800 --> 01:25:27,120
Don’t upset yourself anymore.

1092
01:25:29,280 --> 01:25:31,320
I know this is very hard for you too.

1093
01:25:33,320 --> 01:25:35,760
I’m very tired. Very…

1094
01:25:38,400 --> 01:25:41,439
From
all the endless lies I’ve known as truth…

1095
01:25:41,440 --> 01:25:45,279
…from all these unending evils…

1096
01:25:45,280 --> 01:25:48,160
…from encountering a
different event every day, I’m exhausted.

1097
01:25:49,160 --> 01:25:51,360
Come here.

1098
01:25:56,760 --> 01:25:58,040
You’ll rest here.

1099
01:26:00,480 --> 01:26:01,800
The only place I find peace.

1100
01:26:28,760 --> 01:26:29,760
Disgrace!

1101
01:26:34,400 --> 01:26:35,440
You’re disgraceful.

1102
01:26:37,960 --> 01:26:39,840
I gave you bread for years.

1103
01:26:40,840 --> 01:26:43,040
You even raised your children here.

1104
01:26:45,000 --> 01:26:46,960
Don’t you feel ashamed at all?

1105
01:26:47,080 --> 01:26:49,160
Looking me in the eyes.

1106
01:26:49,360 --> 01:26:51,000
How did you lie to me?

1107
01:26:54,480 --> 01:26:57,120
I didn’t tell
you, Mrs. Nermin, so you wouldn’t be upset.

1108
01:26:57,920 --> 01:26:59,360
Please forgive me.

1109
01:27:00,960 --> 01:27:02,559
Forgive me?

1110
01:27:02,560 --> 01:27:04,200
You don’t have forgiveness, Binnaz.

1111
01:27:05,120 --> 01:27:06,240
You have no forgiveness.

1112
01:27:07,280 --> 01:27:08,839
My child died.

1113
01:27:08,840 --> 01:27:12,360
I couldn’t even pray for him afterward.

1114
01:27:16,000 --> 01:27:18,200
You gave me someone else’s child to hold.

1115
01:27:22,200 --> 01:27:23,840
I lived a lie for years.

1116
01:27:24,680 --> 01:27:25,680
And for years.

1117
01:27:26,960 --> 01:27:28,680
How could you stay silent, woman?

1118
01:27:29,680 --> 01:27:31,200
What did you do behind closed doors?

1119
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:32,880
Did you mock me?

1120
01:27:33,160 --> 01:27:34,240
Did you say “good for you”?

1121
01:27:35,600 --> 01:27:36,600
You’re disgraceful.

1122
01:27:38,280 --> 01:27:41,680
Don’t you feel any shame at all?

1123
01:27:41,880 --> 01:27:43,240
Mom, what are you doing, please?

1124
01:27:43,880 --> 01:27:44,880
Be quiet, Mercan.

1125
01:27:45,920 --> 01:27:47,800
We’ve been raising snakes for years.

1126
01:27:50,320 --> 01:27:52,360
They’ve been mocking us for years.

1127
01:27:55,960 --> 01:27:57,840
Don’t say that, my dear Mrs. Nermin.

1128
01:27:58,520 --> 01:28:03,160
I swear I didn’t tell you to avoid
upsetting you, my dear Mrs. Nermin.

1129
01:28:04,400 --> 01:28:08,840
You were so happy the baby was a boy.

1130
01:28:09,040 --> 01:28:11,440
I didn’t tell to
keep your face from turning cold.

1131
01:28:11,680 --> 01:28:13,000
How would I have known?

1132
01:28:13,080 --> 01:28:14,560
How would I have known that?

1133
01:28:15,040 --> 01:28:18,960
I thought the one you
took from her arms was an orphan.

1134
01:28:19,160 --> 01:28:20,319
I swear.

1135
01:28:20,320 --> 01:28:21,600
How would I have known?

1136
01:28:22,360 --> 01:28:24,560
Haydar told me to stay silent.

1137
01:28:25,040 --> 01:28:28,160
He said, don’t speak,
absolutely don’t speak, Haydar told me.

1138
01:28:29,160 --> 01:28:34,200
My dear Mrs. Nermin,
I’ve carried the guilt for years already.

1139
01:28:35,160 --> 01:28:38,120
Please forgive me, I beg you.

1140
01:28:47,600 --> 01:28:49,760
Sister Binnaz, get up, get up, please.

1141
01:28:50,440 --> 01:28:52,200
Please, go to the kitchen.

1142
01:28:53,200 --> 01:28:55,960
Mercan, my daughter, please forgive me.

1143
01:28:56,840 --> 01:28:57,840
I didn’t know.

1144
01:29:00,200 --> 01:29:03,320
I know, I know, now go ahead.

1145
01:29:08,920 --> 01:29:09,920
Sister Binnaz…

1146
01:29:17,840 --> 01:29:19,880
I understand you, mom.

1147
01:29:21,480 --> 01:29:22,520
Your heart is burning.

1148
01:29:23,400 --> 01:29:24,400
I can see it.

1149
01:29:25,880 --> 01:29:27,880
I’m very
angry too, you’re completely right.

1150
01:29:29,120 --> 01:29:32,240
But Binnaz sister isn’t
responsible for what we’ve been through.

1151
01:29:36,280 --> 01:29:37,280
My father is.

1152
01:29:41,480 --> 01:29:43,000
All of this is his fault.

1153
01:29:52,080 --> 01:29:54,680
He lied to us too much.

1154
01:29:58,160 --> 01:29:59,360
But we’ll endure.

1155
01:30:00,760 --> 01:30:02,240
Nothing has changed for us, mom.

1156
01:30:05,040 --> 01:30:06,960
Murat is still my brother.

1157
01:30:07,640 --> 01:30:09,160
And he’s your son too, okay?

1158
01:30:13,880 --> 01:30:15,880
I need to be alone for a while, Mercan.

1159
01:30:56,040 --> 01:30:57,360
I need to look at this.

1160
01:31:37,040 --> 01:31:39,160
Take it, son, settle the score.

1161
01:31:40,160 --> 01:31:42,400
Since they took your life.

1162
01:31:42,840 --> 01:31:44,720
You’ll take their lives.

1163
01:32:15,000 --> 01:32:16,000
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1164
01:32:17,000 --> 01:32:18,120
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1165
01:32:27,360 --> 01:32:30,080
With these hands, I handed over the weapon.

1166
01:32:30,400 --> 01:32:32,320
With these hands, I killed my son.

1167
01:32:34,680 --> 01:32:35,720
Let go.

1168
01:32:46,840 --> 01:32:48,200
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1169
01:32:51,160 --> 01:32:52,200
Let go.

1170
01:32:52,320 --> 01:32:53,360
No, please.
I said get out.

1171
01:32:53,840 --> 01:32:55,240
I said let go.

1172
01:32:55,280 --> 01:32:56,280
Mrs. Müzeyyen, don’t.

1173
01:33:00,440 --> 01:33:02,120
Mrs. Müzeyyen, please.

1174
01:33:05,080 --> 01:33:07,080
My heart is burning.

1175
01:33:10,080 --> 01:33:12,199
Even
if my hands burned, it wouldn’t be enough.

1176
01:33:12,200 --> 01:33:14,360
Even if
they were cut off, it wouldn’t be enough.

1177
01:33:15,280 --> 01:33:17,000
I buried my child.

1178
01:33:17,080 --> 01:33:19,200
I buried him a second time.

1179
01:33:19,480 --> 01:33:21,680
I caused it to my child.

1180
01:33:31,480 --> 01:33:33,640
I caused it to my child.

1181
01:33:58,000 --> 01:34:01,360
You’ll pay
the price for what you did to my daughter.

1182
01:34:50,160 --> 01:34:52,760
They told me your son was dead.

1183
01:34:53,760 --> 01:34:57,040
He wasn’t, that
Haydar dog swapped the children.

1184
01:35:09,960 --> 01:35:11,640
I never even smelled him once.

1185
01:35:12,040 --> 01:35:14,080
I never even hugged my child once.

1186
01:35:14,960 --> 01:35:16,416
What is he like? Who does he resemble?

1187
01:35:16,440 --> 01:35:18,440
He doesn’t even have a photo, I’ll console
myself.

1188
01:35:28,320 --> 01:35:32,200
How can I live with this pain,
Ateş, how can I live?

1189
01:35:39,400 --> 01:35:41,080
Oh, my child.

1190
01:35:50,840 --> 01:35:52,640
Oh, my child.

1191
01:36:08,160 --> 01:36:09,480
Come, mother.

1192
01:36:11,520 --> 01:36:12,520
Come.

1193
01:36:13,320 --> 01:36:14,600
Lie down, come.

1194
01:36:19,040 --> 01:36:20,080
Come, take off your shoes.

1195
01:36:29,240 --> 01:36:30,360
Are you comfortable, mother?

1196
01:36:34,000 --> 01:36:36,000
There’s no daylight for me anymore.

1197
01:36:42,920 --> 01:36:45,000
There’s no peace for me anymore.

1198
01:36:45,480 --> 01:36:46,480
No tranquility.

1199
01:36:50,000 --> 01:36:51,320
Don’t say that, Mom Müzeyyen.

1200
01:36:52,280 --> 01:36:53,600
These days will pass too.

1201
01:36:56,680 --> 01:36:58,920
Look, we’re here with you.

1202
01:37:00,920 --> 01:37:01,920
We’re here, mom.

1203
01:37:04,640 --> 01:37:06,240
My heart is burning, Ateş.

1204
01:37:06,920 --> 01:37:09,120
It’s even more torn, it doesn’t seem like
it will heal.

1205
01:37:09,960 --> 01:37:11,280
Don’t blame yourself.

1206
01:37:12,280 --> 01:37:14,640
You have no fault in what happened.

1207
01:37:18,600 --> 01:37:19,600
The guilty one is clear.

1208
01:37:20,000 --> 01:37:21,880
He’s already paying the price right now.

1209
01:37:26,200 --> 01:37:28,360
What kind of heartlessness is this, Ateş?

1210
01:37:30,800 --> 01:37:31,800
How?

1211
01:37:37,280 --> 01:37:40,320
Haydar tore
the children from their families.

1212
01:37:46,040 --> 01:37:48,200
Now he’s paying the price for it.

1213
01:37:51,680 --> 01:37:52,960
And he’ll pay more.

1214
01:37:54,360 --> 01:37:55,680
He’ll pay even more.

1215
01:38:04,560 --> 01:38:05,560
You rest now.

1216
01:38:05,720 --> 01:38:06,720
We’re around here.

1217
01:38:08,480 --> 01:38:09,480
Ah, Zehra.

1218
01:38:09,720 --> 01:38:11,040
Mom Müzeyyen, take your medicine.

1219
01:38:11,200 --> 01:38:13,040
Then rest a little, you’ll help her.

1220
01:38:13,080 --> 01:38:14,560
Don’t worry, I’ll take care of it.

1221
01:38:15,320 --> 01:38:16,320
Check frequently.

1222
01:38:17,160 --> 01:38:20,320
Don’t worry, I’ll even make her soup.

1223
01:38:26,720 --> 01:38:28,840
Here you go, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1224
01:38:48,400 --> 01:38:50,120
I never even smelled him once.

1225
01:38:50,560 --> 01:38:52,640
I never even hugged my child once.

1226
01:38:54,240 --> 01:38:57,800
What is he like, who does he resemble, he
doesn’t even have a photo, I’ll console myself.

1227
01:39:36,680 --> 01:39:37,680
How is Mrs. Müzeyyen?

1228
01:39:40,400 --> 01:39:41,960
How would she be, she’s not well.

1229
01:39:42,480 --> 01:39:43,640
She’s resting in her room.

1230
01:39:45,680 --> 01:39:46,880
How about you?

1231
01:39:48,560 --> 01:39:50,040
Of course I’m sad.

1232
01:39:51,400 --> 01:39:53,360
Most of all
for the lives wasted for nothing,

1233
01:39:54,240 --> 01:39:56,000
I’m sad.

1234
01:39:58,640 --> 01:40:00,880
You were hurt too.

1235
01:40:02,240 --> 01:40:03,800
What you learned shook you.

1236
01:40:05,080 --> 01:40:07,880
You think of others, not yourself.

1237
01:40:10,800 --> 01:40:11,800
Do you know?

1238
01:40:15,440 --> 01:40:17,320
Actually, all this time,

1239
01:40:18,320 --> 01:40:21,160
I realized that we
couldn’t be a real family with my family.

1240
01:40:22,880 --> 01:40:23,920
Isn’t it very painful?

1241
01:40:26,160 --> 01:40:28,000
But with all this evil,

1242
01:40:28,200 --> 01:40:31,160
and lies,
there’s no way to speak of a real family.

1243
01:40:42,520 --> 01:40:44,320
What should I do for you?

1244
01:40:48,280 --> 01:40:49,280
Just stay by my side.

1245
01:41:00,280 --> 01:41:01,760
What kind of evil is this?

1246
01:41:04,240 --> 01:41:06,080
How many lives has my father ruined?

1247
01:41:08,520 --> 01:41:10,080
How many people have his deeds cost?

1248
01:41:12,160 --> 01:41:15,080
Who knows how much more innocent
blood is on his hands?

1249
01:41:19,280 --> 01:41:20,280
Eylul.

1250
01:41:21,960 --> 01:41:22,960
My brother.

1251
01:41:28,960 --> 01:41:30,680
How can this man be my father?

1252
01:41:31,640 --> 01:41:34,360
How
did I not realize he was such a bad person?

1253
01:41:35,400 --> 01:41:37,280
One becomes blind to loved ones.

1254
01:41:39,880 --> 01:41:41,360
Evil is always expected from outside.

1255
01:41:42,920 --> 01:41:44,720
That’s why,

1256
01:41:45,800 --> 01:41:48,400
the pain from truths is always greater.

1257
01:41:51,800 --> 01:41:53,320
I’m thinking,

1258
01:41:55,400 --> 01:41:57,280
if my father hadn’t swapped the children,

1259
01:41:59,000 --> 01:42:02,680
if my brother hadn’t lived in this mansion,
hadn’t grown up,

1260
01:42:03,840 --> 01:42:05,480
would he have become that kind of person?

1261
01:42:11,600 --> 01:42:13,320
Is a person born evil,

1262
01:42:15,560 --> 01:42:18,680
or do they become evil later, I don’t know
the answer.

1263
01:42:20,480 --> 01:42:22,680
But there’s only one thing I know.

1264
01:42:25,120 --> 01:42:26,320
Evil is a choice.

1265
01:42:31,920 --> 01:42:33,080
Maybe my brother

1266
01:42:34,120 --> 01:42:36,200
always felt he didn’t belong here.

1267
01:42:38,520 --> 01:42:41,520
Maybe that’s the reason for all his anger.

1268
01:42:43,280 --> 01:42:46,000
I’m sorry, but you’re the
only one who doesn’t belong in this house.

1269
01:42:51,000 --> 01:42:54,160
Could
I also be someone else’s child, I wonder?

1270
01:42:56,240 --> 01:43:00,600
I wish it were so.

1271
01:43:09,960 --> 01:43:12,400
I want a world with only you in it.

1272
01:43:16,120 --> 01:43:17,960
Just keep looking at me like that.

1273
01:43:19,800 --> 01:43:21,720
I’ll rebuild the world anew.

1274
01:43:43,480 --> 01:43:46,760
If you have no claim from Malik,

1275
01:43:47,560 --> 01:43:53,600
you’ll sign this prenuptial agreement.

1276
01:43:57,240 --> 01:44:00,080
You know, in this mansion, not a single day
passes without an incident.

1277
01:44:03,440 --> 01:44:04,440
Can you hear me?

1278
01:44:11,480 --> 01:44:14,960
Mrs. Müzeyyen is very bad, really.

1279
01:44:15,560 --> 01:44:18,520
I’ll
heat up some soup so she can eat something.

1280
01:44:23,160 --> 01:44:26,080
Though I don’t know if she’ll eat.

1281
01:44:46,000 --> 01:44:47,000
Flower!

1282
01:44:50,800 --> 01:44:51,800
Flower!

1283
01:44:57,160 --> 01:44:58,280
Oh God!

1284
01:44:58,560 --> 01:45:02,040
It was bound to happen.
I mean, it was obvious. You…

1285
01:45:03,920 --> 01:45:06,440
What are you thinking, like a little crow?

1286
01:45:07,080 --> 01:45:09,400
Which one
should I tell, which one should I explain?

1287
01:45:09,920 --> 01:45:13,560
Move aside, will
you? You’ll destroy the kitchen otherwise.

1288
01:45:15,000 --> 01:45:16,000
Tell me, what happened?

1289
01:45:17,040 --> 01:45:19,680
This isn’t about Murat,
I understand that. There’s something else.

1290
01:45:20,640 --> 01:45:21,719
But tell me quickly, okay?

1291
01:45:21,720 --> 01:45:24,560
I have to go to Mrs. Müzeyyen. Mr. Ateş
told me not to leave her alone.

1292
01:45:27,640 --> 01:45:28,920
Malik’s mother.

1293
01:45:31,680 --> 01:45:33,360
What did that pharaoh-like woman do again?

1294
01:45:34,640 --> 01:45:36,440
Listen, Malik doesn’t
know, according to her.

1295
01:45:37,480 --> 01:45:39,960
Okay, okay. It will stay between us.

1296
01:45:40,760 --> 01:45:42,040
What happened, what did she say?

1297
01:45:44,960 --> 01:45:47,000
She
asked me to sign the prenuptial agreement.

1298
01:45:47,040 --> 01:45:48,040
What?

1299
01:45:48,320 --> 01:45:50,679
Don’t shout. I said no one knows. Be quiet.

1300
01:45:50,680 --> 01:45:53,040
Oh, I give up, really.

1301
01:45:53,760 --> 01:45:56,320
Honestly, she’s not a snake, she’s a
Şahmeran.

1302
01:45:56,880 --> 01:45:58,440
You should have ripped it off her head.

1303
01:45:58,840 --> 01:46:00,560
I don’t care about money.

1304
01:46:01,720 --> 01:46:03,240
But it hurt me a lot.

1305
01:46:04,840 --> 01:46:06,840
Look at me. Get a grip.

1306
01:46:07,400 --> 01:46:08,720
What do you mean, you don’t care?

1307
01:46:09,840 --> 01:46:12,480
A lucky bird landed on
your head. Are you going to break its wing?

1308
01:46:14,200 --> 01:46:15,200
Don’t be ridiculous.

1309
01:46:16,560 --> 01:46:18,600
Malik wouldn’t want this from you anyway.

1310
01:46:20,680 --> 01:46:22,680
Say I won’t sign, turn your back.

1311
01:46:26,920 --> 01:46:27,920
Okay?

1312
01:47:14,320 --> 01:47:16,640
I never turned my back on you.

1313
01:47:25,200 --> 01:47:27,000
You had hard times too.

1314
01:47:28,760 --> 01:47:30,320
I was by your side.

1315
01:47:37,400 --> 01:47:41,960
I
Chose to believe you, not to question you.

1316
01:47:49,240 --> 01:47:51,360
Don’t you have a single word to say?

1317
01:47:58,920 --> 01:48:00,280
I understand you very well, Demet.

1318
01:48:03,040 --> 01:48:06,119
Not long ago, I was in the same position as
you.

1319
01:48:06,120 --> 01:48:08,120
Stuck in the same limbo.

1320
01:48:14,560 --> 01:48:17,320
I know very well what
it means to choose among loved ones.

1321
01:48:21,840 --> 01:48:22,840
But think like this.

1322
01:48:23,680 --> 01:48:25,520
Maybe I’m doing you a favor right now.

1323
01:48:27,280 --> 01:48:28,280
A favor?

1324
01:48:29,920 --> 01:48:31,000
Think about it, Demet.

1325
01:48:33,160 --> 01:48:35,960
Your brother and
I are two completely opposite poles.

1326
01:48:37,360 --> 01:48:39,120
You, however, are stuck right in
between us.

1327
01:48:40,040 --> 01:48:42,560
Whichever of us you
turn to, your mind will always stay behind.

1328
01:48:45,880 --> 01:48:48,080
I’m just trying to lighten your burden.

1329
01:48:49,120 --> 01:48:50,640
Trust me, I think this is better.

1330
01:48:53,400 --> 01:48:55,480
I wouldn’t expect you to be at the end of
the truth,

1331
01:48:57,080 --> 01:48:58,960
I’d expect you to be by my side.

1332
01:49:26,800 --> 01:49:29,840
Mrs. Müzeyyen is alone too.

1333
01:49:30,960 --> 01:49:32,280
Zehra is taking care of her.

1334
01:49:32,680 --> 01:49:34,960
She gave her
the medicine. She’s probably sleeping now.

1335
01:49:35,520 --> 01:49:36,720
I’ll go check on her in a bit.

1336
01:49:44,280 --> 01:49:45,840
Yes, I’m listening.

1337
01:49:49,360 --> 01:49:52,080
Um, I want to tell you something.

1338
01:49:52,800 --> 01:49:55,680
I already understand that.
Go ahead, I’m waiting.

1339
01:49:56,400 --> 01:49:59,760
But no anger. Don’t
reject without thinking.

1340
01:50:01,680 --> 01:50:04,720
If there’s
bargaining, the matter is serious. Tell me.

1341
01:50:09,960 --> 01:50:12,160
I say Aslı should come to the mansion.

1342
01:50:14,320 --> 01:50:15,320
No.

1343
01:50:16,120 --> 01:50:20,120
See? You immediately reject without
listening or thinking.

1344
01:50:20,440 --> 01:50:22,080
There’s nothing to think about, Mercan.

1345
01:50:24,960 --> 01:50:27,160
I’m still very angry at Aslı.

1346
01:50:27,800 --> 01:50:28,920
In fact, I’m the angriest.

1347
01:50:30,160 --> 01:50:31,320
And I have every right to be.

1348
01:50:32,400 --> 01:50:34,360
I suffered from what she did, you know.

1349
01:50:36,320 --> 01:50:38,040
But you saw Mrs. Müzeyyen’s state.

1350
01:50:39,200 --> 01:50:41,720
Right now, neither you nor anyone else can
help her.

1351
01:50:42,600 --> 01:50:44,840
She needs to be with her daughter.

1352
01:50:49,280 --> 01:50:51,920
I don’t want anyone else harmed
because of my father.

1353
01:50:52,920 --> 01:50:54,960
I can’t bear another load of guilt.

1354
01:51:02,720 --> 01:51:04,640
Your friend has come. Take care of him.

1355
01:51:11,040 --> 01:51:12,760
Because of me?

1356
01:51:14,040 --> 01:51:17,039
No, not because of you.

1357
01:51:17,040 --> 01:51:20,760
It’s another matter. But we’ll handle it.

1358
01:51:21,960 --> 01:51:23,400
Welcome. Sit, come.

1359
01:51:24,480 --> 01:51:27,520
Thank you, but I didn’t come willingly.

1360
01:51:28,400 --> 01:51:31,240
You shouldn’t have insisted so much.

1361
01:51:31,280 --> 01:51:32,880
I insisted, and here you are.

1362
01:51:34,680 --> 01:51:36,000
I won’t leave you alone.

1363
01:51:39,000 --> 01:51:40,840
We have wedding preparations ahead too.

1364
01:51:41,960 --> 01:51:43,240
I can’t manage without you.

1365
01:51:44,960 --> 01:51:46,520
You know what happened recently.

1366
01:51:48,000 --> 01:51:50,200
Staying here isn’t right.

1367
01:51:51,440 --> 01:51:53,400
I no longer know what’s right or wrong.

1368
01:51:54,240 --> 01:51:55,920
The decision was made, and here you are.

1369
01:51:59,120 --> 01:52:02,120
I’ve also thought
about myself a little, honestly.

1370
01:52:04,200 --> 01:52:05,960
Of
Course, you don’t know the recent events.

1371
01:52:07,040 --> 01:52:09,760
Events? What events?

1372
01:52:11,800 --> 01:52:13,960
God, what a life we’re living.

1373
01:52:21,560 --> 01:52:23,560
I sent you the list of all addresses.

1374
01:52:23,800 --> 01:52:24,800
Did you check everywhere?

1375
01:52:29,000 --> 01:52:30,600
I don’t understand these things, friend.

1376
01:52:30,960 --> 01:52:34,000
If necessary, go in and take the men by the
nape like a needle hole.

1377
01:52:39,440 --> 01:52:40,480
I can handle a task.

1378
01:52:40,840 --> 01:52:41,960
No news from Nezir, right?

1379
01:52:43,680 --> 01:52:46,160
None. As if he swallowed the ground.

1380
01:52:47,560 --> 01:52:49,760
We’ll turn the underground and the surface
upside down.

1381
01:52:50,840 --> 01:52:51,960
It won’t be easy, obviously.

1382
01:52:52,840 --> 01:52:54,640
Underestimating him would be a mistake.

1383
01:52:56,280 --> 01:52:57,840
But the more tricks a hunter knows…

1384
01:53:00,200 --> 01:53:02,600
…the more paths a bear knows.

1385
01:53:04,040 --> 01:53:05,160
This job is taking too long.

1386
01:53:06,080 --> 01:53:07,880
We’ll solve it, God willing, soon.

1387
01:53:11,840 --> 01:53:13,960
There’s more than one problem to deal with.

1388
01:53:15,160 --> 01:53:16,360
This isn’t about Murat, right?

1389
01:53:18,000 --> 01:53:19,000
Damn Haydar.

1390
01:53:19,680 --> 01:53:22,400
Who knows
how many families’ fires he’s extinguished?

1391
01:53:26,880 --> 01:53:28,800
He
Even takes the child of the man he killed.

1392
01:53:29,520 --> 01:53:31,360
The
mother thinks her child is dead for years.

1393
01:53:31,560 --> 01:53:33,200
She mourns, swears revenge.

1394
01:53:34,000 --> 01:53:35,800
Then one day she finds out it was all lies.

1395
01:53:36,120 --> 01:53:37,600
What kind of heartlessness is this?

1396
01:53:38,640 --> 01:53:41,040
If Murat had grown up with his own family…

1397
01:53:41,640 --> 01:53:43,960
…maybe none of this would have happened.

1398
01:53:44,320 --> 01:53:44,720
Right?

1399
01:53:45,320 --> 01:53:47,000
It’s as if everything is tangled together.

1400
01:53:48,320 --> 01:53:50,760
But how do we restrain Mrs. Müzeyyen now?

1401
01:53:51,400 --> 01:53:53,320
She literally killed her
son with her own hands.

1402
01:53:54,720 --> 01:53:57,320
Oh God, oh!

1403
01:54:02,120 --> 01:54:03,920
It’s impossible to ease her pain.

1404
01:54:09,360 --> 01:54:12,840
Nothing can be done but to be by her side.

1405
01:54:17,360 --> 01:54:18,600
My mind still can’t grasp it.

1406
01:54:20,960 --> 01:54:22,720
Haydar’s evil has no limits.

1407
01:54:30,640 --> 01:54:32,920
Mercan wants to call Aslı to the mansion.

1408
01:54:34,880 --> 01:54:36,480
I thought about it too, actually…

1409
01:54:37,040 --> 01:54:39,880
You barely see Aslı’s face.

1410
01:54:40,360 --> 01:54:41,760
But I think we should call her.

1411
01:54:42,560 --> 01:54:45,960
Because in this period, only her
own daughter can understand Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1412
01:54:53,800 --> 01:54:56,039
No matter what we say or do…

1413
01:54:56,040 --> 01:54:57,680
…it won’t be like her, that’s true.

1414
01:55:15,920 --> 01:55:17,120
Brother, everything is ready.

1415
01:55:17,880 --> 01:55:19,480
The children found someone trustworthy.

1416
01:55:19,880 --> 01:55:21,040
The captain is set.

1417
01:55:21,200 --> 01:55:22,240
The timing is arranged.

1418
01:55:23,120 --> 01:55:24,120
Okay.

1419
01:55:24,480 --> 01:55:25,560
Let them wait a bit longer.

1420
01:55:27,240 --> 01:55:28,840
The police are on our tail.

1421
01:55:29,480 --> 01:55:30,720
They’ve blocked all the roads.

1422
01:55:31,360 --> 01:55:32,840
The Karahans on the other side too.

1423
01:55:33,760 --> 01:55:34,520
If this opportunity is missed…

1424
01:55:34,521 --> 01:55:35,800
Let it be missed, brother.

1425
01:55:36,560 --> 01:55:37,640
Let it be missed.

1426
01:55:38,240 --> 01:55:39,600
You can create another one.

1427
01:55:40,320 --> 01:55:41,760
Do you think I feed you for nothing?

1428
01:55:45,160 --> 01:55:49,040
No going anywhere without sending Ateş to
the grave and taking Mercan.

1429
01:55:51,320 --> 01:55:52,720
And we have our wedding too.

1430
01:55:53,560 --> 01:55:54,760
I must attend it.

1431
01:55:55,440 --> 01:55:56,880
Otherwise it would be very improper.

1432
01:56:50,960 --> 01:56:53,320
Ateş, is what I heard true?

1433
01:56:56,240 --> 01:56:58,360
Murat is my brother.

1434
01:57:01,680 --> 01:57:02,680
Yes.

1435
01:57:05,960 --> 01:57:07,160
We’re shocked too.

1436
01:57:14,640 --> 01:57:16,280
Your mother needs you.

1437
01:57:21,440 --> 01:57:23,239
You’re here at the mansion because Mercan
wants it.

1438
01:57:23,240 --> 01:57:25,520
If it were up to me, you’d be in prison.

1439
01:57:27,320 --> 01:57:30,440
I don’t want to see you wandering around.

1440
01:57:35,360 --> 01:57:37,560
If you make one more mistake…

1441
01:57:38,240 --> 01:57:40,640
…you’ll go back to where you came from.

1442
01:57:41,240 --> 01:57:42,240
Keep that in mind.

1443
01:57:49,800 --> 01:57:50,800
Thank you.

1444
01:57:57,440 --> 01:57:58,640
Aslı.

1445
01:57:59,720 --> 01:58:00,720
Mom?

1446
01:58:04,560 --> 01:58:06,440
You found out, right?

1447
01:58:07,360 --> 01:58:08,640
You learned about Murat.

1448
01:58:29,840 --> 01:58:31,480
How’s my flower today?

1449
01:58:33,280 --> 01:58:34,280
How could she be?

1450
01:58:34,920 --> 01:58:35,920
Good, like that.

1451
01:58:36,600 --> 01:58:37,720
I’m just sitting here.

1452
01:58:58,200 --> 01:58:59,200
What happened?

1453
01:58:59,440 --> 01:59:00,640
Did her blood pressure drop?

1454
01:59:00,800 --> 01:59:02,480
It dropped, don’t worry.

1455
01:59:02,840 --> 01:59:03,840
Thank God.

1456
01:59:04,400 --> 01:59:06,840
And love to you too.

1457
01:59:07,080 --> 01:59:08,800
You pressed her too much.

1458
01:59:12,720 --> 01:59:14,520
Are we the guilty ones now?

1459
01:59:16,240 --> 01:59:18,559
Of course, the lies weren’t told to you.

1460
01:59:18,560 --> 01:59:19,560
How nice.

1461
01:59:20,320 --> 01:59:21,520
I think Zehra is right.

1462
01:59:22,680 --> 01:59:23,520
Didn’t you see?

1463
01:59:23,640 --> 01:59:24,920
She was very sad.

1464
01:59:25,280 --> 01:59:27,520
I don’t think
she would have lied if she didn’t have to.

1465
01:59:28,000 --> 01:59:29,680
We’re talking about Aunt Binnaz.

1466
01:59:29,920 --> 01:59:31,760
Did you never know your mother?

1467
01:59:34,760 --> 01:59:37,920
If I were in
her place, I wouldn’t have said it either.

1468
01:59:38,800 --> 01:59:41,279
Imagine facing Haydar Yıldırım…

1469
01:59:41,280 --> 01:59:42,959
…and he told you to remain silent.

1470
01:59:42,960 --> 01:59:45,240
Tell her if you can.

1471
01:59:46,160 --> 01:59:47,960
She was helpless
because she cared about you.

1472
01:59:48,680 --> 01:59:50,600
Who
knows what pains she endured all this time.

1473
01:59:54,200 --> 01:59:56,160
This burden must
have been heavy for her already.

1474
01:59:56,360 --> 01:59:57,720
Honestly, I don’t know about that.

1475
01:59:57,960 --> 01:59:59,400
You need to win your mother’s favor.

1476
02:00:03,240 --> 02:00:04,240
I think so too.

1477
02:01:06,480 --> 02:01:08,480
Who’s there?

1478
02:01:25,280 --> 02:01:32,280
My son… my son… my dear…

1479
02:01:34,920 --> 02:01:42,920
My son… my dear…

1480
02:01:59,480 --> 02:02:00,480
My son!

1481
02:02:23,400 --> 02:02:24,480
Where are you?

1482
02:02:25,600 --> 02:02:26,600
Here I am, what’s up?

1483
02:02:28,080 --> 02:02:29,880
You won’t leave my sight again.

1484
02:02:30,440 --> 02:02:32,079
Not a single step without my knowledge.

1485
02:02:32,080 --> 02:02:34,080
Where did that come from?

1486
02:02:35,480 --> 02:02:37,119
When Aslı entered this mansion…

1487
02:02:37,120 --> 02:02:39,159
Sorry…

1488
02:02:39,160 --> 02:02:40,720
…I didn’t find my wife on the way.

1489
02:02:41,200 --> 02:02:43,000
You wanted this.

1490
02:02:44,440 --> 02:02:46,120
Don’t laugh, I’m serious.

1491
02:02:47,240 --> 02:02:49,439
Okay, I understand your concern, but…

1492
02:02:49,440 --> 02:02:50,480
Should we not exaggerate?

1493
02:02:51,200 --> 02:02:55,160
Let’s exaggerate, my
dear. As much as we can.

1494
02:02:55,840 --> 02:02:59,000
We remove one danger and
bring the other closer.

1495
02:02:59,520 --> 02:03:01,679
That’s why we exaggerate as much as we can.

1496
02:03:01,680 --> 02:03:02,680
Okay?

1497
02:03:05,560 --> 02:03:06,680
Am I really your life?

1498
02:03:08,760 --> 02:03:09,880
I’m very serious.

1499
02:03:10,120 --> 02:03:11,520
And very determined.

1500
02:03:12,480 --> 02:03:13,720
My husband would think of me.

1501
02:03:15,480 --> 02:03:16,720
I will think of you, of course.

1502
02:03:17,360 --> 02:03:18,919
If a stone hits your foot…

1503
02:03:18,920 --> 02:03:20,280
…I’ll feel it too.

1504
02:03:21,320 --> 02:03:22,320
Do you realize that?

1505
02:03:22,760 --> 02:03:23,760
Of course.

1506
02:03:25,000 --> 02:03:26,280
Because it’s the same for me.

1507
02:03:27,240 --> 02:03:29,720
I won’t allow harm to you or myself.

1508
02:03:30,680 --> 02:03:33,400
Don’t
underestimate my strength. Do you see this?

1509
02:03:35,080 --> 02:03:36,080
Your strength, huh?

1510
02:03:37,400 --> 02:03:38,400
That’s what you say.

1511
02:03:38,880 --> 02:03:41,320
Here, take some strength.

1512
02:03:41,960 --> 02:03:43,440
What are you doing? Put me down.

1513
02:03:44,280 --> 02:03:45,280
Ateş!

1514
02:03:57,200 --> 02:03:58,400
What will you do now?

1515
02:04:17,520 --> 02:04:19,120
You cheated.

1516
02:04:20,200 --> 02:04:22,360
All’s fair in war and love.

1517
02:04:24,400 --> 02:04:25,640
Where does your path lead?

1518
02:04:26,840 --> 02:04:28,000
Always to you.

1519
02:04:43,000 --> 02:04:44,600
I love you.

1520
02:04:48,400 --> 02:04:49,520
I love you so much.

1521
02:05:15,160 --> 02:05:16,320
My wife, come.

1522
02:05:21,640 --> 02:05:22,800
Come on.
Okay, brother-in-law.

1523
02:05:23,040 --> 02:05:24,040
Come on, my dear.

1524
02:05:24,400 --> 02:05:25,680
Don’t give him a moment’s peace.

1525
02:05:25,880 --> 02:05:27,640
You make the girl cook
the eggs beautifully.

1526
02:05:28,840 --> 02:05:30,040
I’m already doing it.

1527
02:05:30,560 --> 02:05:31,840
If I do it, it will be perfect.

1528
02:05:33,200 --> 02:05:34,200
My wife.

1529
02:05:34,360 --> 02:05:35,360
My husband.

1530
02:05:39,040 --> 02:05:39,440
Like this.
Look.

1531
02:05:39,840 --> 02:05:41,840
Preparing breakfast is an art.

1532
02:05:42,680 --> 02:05:45,760
I always do it, my dear.

1533
02:05:46,320 --> 02:05:47,440
Of course, of course.

1534
02:05:51,840 --> 02:05:53,120
Brother, pay attention.

1535
02:05:56,760 --> 02:06:00,600
My daughter, it was
an accident, bad luck happened. It happens.

1536
02:06:01,160 --> 02:06:03,600
Accident? Call it clumsiness.

1537
02:06:03,960 --> 02:06:06,519
We wanted to prepare
the table and surprise her before she woke.

1538
02:06:06,520 --> 02:06:07,800
You’ll ruin everything.

1539
02:06:07,880 --> 02:06:11,360
Okay, fine, but why are
you shouting, friends?

1540
02:06:13,160 --> 02:06:14,256
They’re shouting, partner, don’t you see?

1541
02:06:14,280 --> 02:06:15,960
What’s happening? What came upon us again?

1542
02:06:17,720 --> 02:06:19,480
Mom, calm down, nothing happened.

1543
02:06:19,680 --> 02:06:20,040
Nothing at all.

1544
02:06:20,280 --> 02:06:23,000
We wanted to
prepare breakfast for you to cheer you up.

1545
02:06:23,120 --> 02:06:24,800
But my brother’s clumsiness struck.

1546
02:06:26,960 --> 02:06:27,960
Daughter.

1547
02:06:28,520 --> 02:06:30,960
Your voice is louder than my plate.

1548
02:06:32,320 --> 02:06:34,759
We wanted to surprise
her after a long time.

1549
02:06:34,760 --> 02:06:36,760
We messed everything up.

1550
02:06:36,920 --> 02:06:38,800
Brother, you’re both guilty and strong.

1551
02:06:39,960 --> 02:06:41,560
We just wanted someone to be happy.

1552
02:06:41,840 --> 02:06:42,880
You ruined everything.

1553
02:06:43,040 --> 02:06:44,360
Weren’t we supposed to apologize?

1554
02:06:45,080 --> 02:06:46,080
Berat, be quiet.

1555
02:06:46,440 --> 02:06:48,600
You’re just
going to take this plate and put it there.

1556
02:06:48,640 --> 02:06:49,880
It shouldn’t be this hard.

1557
02:06:51,480 --> 02:06:52,440
This woman…

1558
02:06:52,441 --> 02:06:53,919
…after all these years…

1559
02:06:53,920 --> 02:06:56,080
…prepared the table for us without a single
complaint.

1560
02:06:56,720 --> 02:06:58,720
Did it ruin our mood? No.

1561
02:06:58,760 --> 02:07:01,000
We
Wanted to do something, to make her happy.

1562
02:07:01,080 --> 02:07:02,640
No, we couldn’t. It didn’t work out.

1563
02:07:04,760 --> 02:07:06,320
Always from the plate.

1564
02:07:06,800 --> 02:07:09,040
From the plate, of course. From the plate.

1565
02:07:25,160 --> 02:07:26,280
Binnaz mother? Are you okay?

1566
02:07:28,960 --> 02:07:29,960
You’re clumsy.

1567
02:07:30,240 --> 02:07:31,240
Mom.

1568
02:07:31,880 --> 02:07:33,360
Why are you crying?

1569
02:07:34,400 --> 02:07:35,400
Mother.

1570
02:07:35,760 --> 02:07:37,080
Mother, what happened?

1571
02:07:39,800 --> 02:07:41,920
We did it so you’d be happy.

1572
02:07:44,960 --> 02:07:46,400
Always from the plate.

1573
02:07:46,880 --> 02:07:47,880
Oh brother.

1574
02:07:52,000 --> 02:07:54,000
Thank you, my beautiful children.

1575
02:07:59,760 --> 02:08:00,880
May you always exist.

1576
02:08:03,080 --> 02:08:04,160
You too, Binnaz mother.

1577
02:08:04,480 --> 02:08:05,839
Oh my dear mother.

1578
02:08:05,840 --> 02:08:06,840
My dear mother.

1579
02:08:11,960 --> 02:08:12,960
Brother-in-law.

1580
02:08:15,840 --> 02:08:17,600
Okay daughter, go. I’ll hug too.

1581
02:08:17,760 --> 02:08:18,760
Go, come on.

1582
02:08:19,040 --> 02:08:20,600
You hug like this, I’ll hug like that.

1583
02:08:22,120 --> 02:08:25,000
Okay, enough, that’s enough for us all.

1584
02:08:40,880 --> 02:08:41,880
Mercan?

1585
02:08:52,280 --> 02:08:54,440
Why did this have to be so difficult?

1586
02:09:08,320 --> 02:09:12,640
If I’m Mercan, I win this battle.

1587
02:09:30,840 --> 02:09:33,280
How long have you been here?

1588
02:09:34,120 --> 02:09:35,720
Come here, come.

1589
02:09:38,640 --> 02:09:41,040
I don’t understand how you even fight over
a zipper.

1590
02:09:41,720 --> 02:09:43,720
I can fight over anything that annoys me.

1591
02:09:45,000 --> 02:09:46,040
I already understood that.

1592
02:09:51,880 --> 02:09:52,880
How is that possible?

1593
02:09:55,480 --> 02:09:57,880
Sometimes it’s not about fighting…

1594
02:09:59,400 --> 02:10:00,400
…it’s about loving.

1595
02:10:05,440 --> 02:10:06,560
You’re my hero.

1596
02:10:07,640 --> 02:10:08,920
Well done, champ.

1597
02:10:09,800 --> 02:10:10,800
What was that now?

1598
02:10:11,280 --> 02:10:12,920
I said love, not hit.

1599
02:10:20,720 --> 02:10:22,240
You’re my hero.

1600
02:10:23,960 --> 02:10:24,960
Now it’s done.

1601
02:10:26,000 --> 02:10:27,000
Anything else?

1602
02:10:29,080 --> 02:10:30,080
Then…

1603
02:10:30,800 --> 02:10:32,200
Today’s omelets are on me.

1604
02:10:32,560 --> 02:10:33,600
I think you deserved this.

1605
02:10:34,920 --> 02:10:36,720
I feel like I always deserve this.

1606
02:10:39,360 --> 02:10:40,360
Okay, come on.

1607
02:10:40,960 --> 02:10:42,960
Get dressed and go downstairs quickly.

1608
02:10:44,040 --> 02:10:45,080
At your service, my queen.

1609
02:11:29,720 --> 02:11:30,720
Welcome.

1610
02:11:32,920 --> 02:11:34,520
You said it was important, so I came.

1611
02:11:34,920 --> 02:11:36,120
Good, you did the right thing.

1612
02:11:41,960 --> 02:11:42,960
What?

1613
02:11:43,840 --> 02:11:44,840
What’s important?

1614
02:11:46,360 --> 02:11:48,560
Actually, it may not even be important.

1615
02:11:48,840 --> 02:11:50,080
It depends on the person.

1616
02:11:50,360 --> 02:11:52,641
What seems important to
me may not seem important to you.

1617
02:11:52,840 --> 02:11:53,840
Cemal!

1618
02:11:54,160 --> 02:11:55,160
What happened?

1619
02:12:00,440 --> 02:12:01,480
What’s this?

1620
02:12:04,320 --> 02:12:05,520
Here it is…
I got this for you.

1621
02:12:08,640 --> 02:12:09,920
What does it say in the picture?

1622
02:12:13,360 --> 02:12:14,360
Sushi.

1623
02:12:16,680 --> 02:12:17,680
This one.
What is it?

1624
02:12:18,040 --> 02:12:19,400
It’s written there, can’t you see?

1625
02:12:23,120 --> 02:12:24,320
You like it, right?

1626
02:12:24,400 --> 02:12:26,040
I got it because you eat it all the time.

1627
02:12:26,280 --> 02:12:27,880
Come on, eat one.

1628
02:12:28,840 --> 02:12:29,840
No.

1629
02:12:51,320 --> 02:12:54,800
Did you really drink tea with sushi?

1630
02:13:02,120 --> 02:13:05,640
At least I like one of them.

1631
02:13:06,520 --> 02:13:07,520
Cemal.

1632
02:13:08,680 --> 02:13:09,720
I’m very happy.

1633
02:13:10,120 --> 02:13:12,080
But I
can’t eat sushi first thing in the morning.

1634
02:13:12,160 --> 02:13:14,080
Come
on, let’s have a proper breakfast together.

1635
02:13:14,360 --> 02:13:14,880
Okay?

1636
02:13:15,160 --> 02:13:16,320
Bless your mind, Demet.

1637
02:13:16,440 --> 02:13:18,480
Let me kiss your mouth.

1638
02:13:31,640 --> 02:13:32,640
Egg.

1639
02:13:37,080 --> 02:13:39,040
That will do the job.

1640
02:13:39,720 --> 02:13:41,120
Let’s make an omelet.

1641
02:13:41,560 --> 02:13:42,560
Good, let’s do it.

1642
02:13:43,280 --> 02:13:45,000
Let’s remove this from here.

1643
02:13:45,160 --> 02:13:46,200
We won’t eat this anymore.

1644
02:13:51,800 --> 02:13:53,000
Let me take this out.

1645
02:13:53,120 --> 02:13:54,440
I can’t make it with this anyway.

1646
02:13:57,000 --> 02:13:57,800
How many eggs should we use?

1647
02:13:57,840 --> 02:13:58,840
Two, three.

1648
02:13:59,360 --> 02:14:00,360
Three, I think.

1649
02:14:01,200 --> 02:14:02,720
I already thought three.

1650
02:14:04,120 --> 02:14:05,920
I
Couldn’t taste anything from the one I ate.

1651
02:14:08,520 --> 02:14:10,040
These two.

1652
02:14:14,520 --> 02:14:15,520
And this is three.

1653
02:14:17,800 --> 02:14:19,960
Now let’s whisk this nicely.

1654
02:14:20,880 --> 02:14:22,120
Come, the whisk is here.

1655
02:14:22,760 --> 02:14:24,040
I was looking for it anyway.

1656
02:14:24,960 --> 02:14:25,960
Thanks.

1657
02:14:29,600 --> 02:14:30,600
Whisk well.

1658
02:14:47,240 --> 02:14:48,560
That’s done.

1659
02:14:49,920 --> 02:14:51,560
Let me get a pan.

1660
02:15:04,920 --> 02:15:06,440
Let’s put it like this.

1661
02:15:16,720 --> 02:15:18,320
The eggs are here.

1662
02:15:19,480 --> 02:15:24,560
First, let’s add some oil.

1663
02:15:46,800 --> 02:15:50,040
That should be enough.

1664
02:16:01,600 --> 02:16:02,640
Should I add chili flakes?

1665
02:16:03,440 --> 02:16:04,440
Sure.

1666
02:16:04,680 --> 02:16:05,440
But not too much.

1667
02:16:05,441 --> 02:16:07,640
Spice is good. I’ll add a bit more, look.

1668
02:16:10,440 --> 02:16:11,440
Add it.

1669
02:16:16,040 --> 02:16:18,880
Salt is a must anyway, you know.

1670
02:16:28,720 --> 02:16:32,280
By the way, that wasn’t
chili flakes you added, it was sumac.

1671
02:16:42,320 --> 02:16:43,640
That’s fine, we’ll eat it.

1672
02:16:44,640 --> 02:16:47,680
Of course we will, what difference does it
make?

1673
02:17:16,960 --> 02:17:18,680
How many eggs should I crack?

1674
02:17:20,960 --> 02:17:22,000
Three should be enough.

1675
02:17:31,320 --> 02:17:39,320
[MERCAN SINGING]

1676
02:18:00,800 --> 02:18:02,560
Oops.

1677
02:18:10,480 --> 02:18:18,480
[MERCAN SINGING]
